WEBVTT

00:12.946 --> 00:14.892
[ Explosion ]

00:20.521 --> 00:21.864
Perfect.

00:21.855 --> 00:24.335
They ought to be happy
with that one.

00:24.324 --> 00:25.530
Two more to come.

00:25.526 --> 00:27.028
Let's wait for 'em.

00:27.327 --> 00:29.238
[ Explosion ]

00:32.533 --> 00:33.705
Was that thunder?

00:33.700 --> 00:34.701
Sure hope so.

00:34.701 --> 00:35.975
We could use
some rain around here.

00:35.969 --> 00:37.141
I don't know,
sounded more like

00:37.137 --> 00:38.548
an explosion to me.

00:38.539 --> 00:40.018
Come on, ladies.
You know the drill.

00:40.007 --> 00:41.680
Do we ever, Screw.

00:43.877 --> 00:45.857
♪♪

00:48.682 --> 00:50.662
[ Explosion ]

01:03.430 --> 01:05.410
[ Explosions ]

01:10.571 --> 01:12.517
[ Snarling ]

01:16.777 --> 01:18.757
[ Water splashes ]

01:34.728 --> 01:36.537
It's Miller time.

01:36.530 --> 01:38.066
Beer?

01:38.065 --> 01:39.203
It's only 11:00.

01:39.199 --> 01:42.146
We've been at this since,
what, 7:00 A.M.?

01:42.135 --> 01:43.307
Yeah.

01:43.303 --> 01:45.579
Four hours
under the broiling sun,

01:45.572 --> 01:48.280
ain't a real man
deserve a brewski?

01:48.275 --> 01:49.379
Guess so.

01:49.376 --> 01:51.447
- I know so.
- So where, then?

01:51.445 --> 01:54.449
- Archway?
- Forget it.

01:54.448 --> 01:55.825
The beer's always
lukewarm over there.

01:55.816 --> 01:57.921
- That's true.
- I'm thinking Tommy's.

01:57.918 --> 01:59.761
But that's ten miles
out of our way.

01:59.753 --> 02:02.597
Not if we cut across
the stream over here.

02:02.589 --> 02:05.126
I know a shortcut that will
get us there in half the time.

02:05.125 --> 02:06.433
You think you can make it
through that?

02:06.426 --> 02:08.633
- It's a bog out there.
- It's not that deep.

02:08.628 --> 02:10.609
I have a four-wheel drive.

02:10.597 --> 02:12.907
So fine. It's not my ride.

02:12.899 --> 02:14.469
Go for it.

02:14.468 --> 02:15.970
Hold on then.

02:16.169 --> 02:17.842
[ Engine starts ]

02:27.948 --> 02:29.859
♪♪

02:36.690 --> 02:38.795
You're not gonna make it, Sam.
It's too deep.

02:38.792 --> 02:40.863
Oh, yeah? Watch this.

02:52.806 --> 02:54.717
[Tire squeals]

02:55.642 --> 02:57.553
♪♪

03:04.317 --> 03:06.228
[ Tires squealing ]

03:08.989 --> 03:11.526
Ah, yeah. I'm watching.
I'm watching.

03:12.192 --> 03:14.468
♪♪

03:14.661 --> 03:16.800
Fred, I have it under control.

03:20.901 --> 03:22.847
[Water splashing ]

03:23.503 --> 03:24.641
Hey...

03:25.672 --> 03:26.810
what's that?

03:30.010 --> 03:31.683
[ Screams ]

03:32.546 --> 03:34.492
♪♪

05:32.465 --> 05:34.342
[ Boat motor whirring ]

05:54.788 --> 05:56.165
See anything?

05:56.156 --> 05:57.635
Not yet.

05:57.624 --> 05:59.035
I doubt we will.

05:59.025 --> 06:00.060
Racket from that motor

06:00.060 --> 06:02.540
gives 'em plenty of time
to lay low.

06:02.529 --> 06:05.339
- You want me to turn back?
- Give it a few more minutes.

06:05.332 --> 06:06.333
You got it, boss.

06:08.235 --> 06:09.578
There. You see it?

06:09.569 --> 06:11.674
No, can't say that I do.

06:11.671 --> 06:15.175
Lake to the right.
Water's all muddy.

06:17.544 --> 06:19.421
That could be
where they went ashore.

06:19.412 --> 06:21.050
Head over there.

06:21.047 --> 06:21.991
Will do.

06:23.049 --> 06:24.050
And kill the motor.

06:24.050 --> 06:27.190
- How am I supposed to--
- Stroke.

06:27.187 --> 06:28.222
Really?

06:28.221 --> 06:30.098
Worked for the Indians,
didn't it?

06:30.323 --> 06:32.428
[ Motor shuts off]

06:35.028 --> 06:36.507
Whatever you say, chief.

06:36.696 --> 06:38.607
[ Water splashes ]

06:43.069 --> 06:45.015
[ Birds chirping ]

06:55.582 --> 06:59.257
Somebody's been here lately.
Grass and vines all trampled.

06:59.252 --> 07:00.560
Eh, you think it was them?

07:00.553 --> 07:02.396
Maybe. Maybe not.

07:02.389 --> 07:03.891
You know, that's what
I love about you, boss.

07:03.890 --> 07:06.234
You're very noncommittal.

07:06.226 --> 07:08.228
Men are noncammittal, Adam.

07:08.228 --> 07:09.639
Women are...

07:09.629 --> 07:10.937
well, let's just say
we're mysterious.

07:10.931 --> 07:13.207
All right.
All right, I'll remember that.

07:13.199 --> 07:14.200
You da that,

07:14.200 --> 07:15.304
you'll make
Detective First Grade

07:15.302 --> 07:16.781
in no time at all.

07:16.770 --> 07:18.545
All right, so now what?

07:18.538 --> 07:20.074
Look for clues, silly.

07:20.073 --> 07:21.984
You go right. I'll go left.

07:21.975 --> 07:24.114
- And?
- And watch your butt.

07:24.110 --> 07:25.418
If those guys
are still around here,

07:25.412 --> 07:26.789
they're armed and dangerous.

07:26.780 --> 07:28.885
You don't think those guys
are gonna stick around here,

07:28.882 --> 07:30.418
do you,
with all that money on 'em?

07:30.417 --> 07:31.725
No telling what they'll do.

07:31.718 --> 07:32.788
My last partner
got complacent,

07:32.786 --> 07:34.288
did a year in rehab.

07:34.287 --> 07:36.233
All right,
well, if I find anything,

07:36.222 --> 07:38.998
- I'll come get you.
- You do that.

07:40.493 --> 07:43.133
♪♪

08:10.123 --> 08:12.103
[ Bird chirping ]

08:24.671 --> 08:26.617
[ Music swells]

08:44.791 --> 08:45.963
[ Gasps ]

08:46.159 --> 08:47.695
Whoa. Whoa.

08:47.694 --> 08:50.174
Kid, you almost
got yourself shot.

08:50.163 --> 08:51.904
Come on. There's something
you gotta get a look at.

08:51.898 --> 08:53.536
What is it?

08:53.533 --> 08:55.069
Best you see it for yourself.

08:55.068 --> 08:57.309
This better be good.

09:01.408 --> 09:03.319
[ Insects buzzing ]

09:05.912 --> 09:08.518
Woman:
What the hell happened here?

09:08.515 --> 09:11.724
Got me. I mean, looks like
somebody was torn apart.

09:15.522 --> 09:18.765
[ Insects buzzing louder ]

09:21.494 --> 09:23.030
Gator, maybe?

09:23.229 --> 09:25.072
No. I grew up in these parts.

09:25.265 --> 09:27.836
I ain't ever seen a gator
do anything like that.

09:27.834 --> 09:29.245
What, then?

09:29.402 --> 09:31.279
[ Man groans]

09:44.884 --> 09:46.557
[ Screams ]

09:46.753 --> 09:49.233
Shark. Sh-sh-shark.

09:49.222 --> 09:51.896
Sh-sh-sh-shark.

09:51.891 --> 09:53.461
Uh...

09:53.460 --> 09:57.067
- I'm gonna go call this in.
- You do that.

09:57.063 --> 10:00.533
Sh-sh-sh-shark. Shark.

10:01.034 --> 10:02.945
[ Water rushing ]

10:15.248 --> 10:16.955
Relax, rookie.

10:16.950 --> 10:18.054
This is a slack assignment.

10:18.051 --> 10:19.291
The only thing
you gotta worry about

10:19.285 --> 10:20.263
is the heat.

10:20.253 --> 10:21.994
Yeah, a walk in the park.

10:21.988 --> 10:23.626
Get out your paperwork.
We're almost there.

10:25.325 --> 10:27.896
♪♪

10:43.443 --> 10:45.354
[ Brakes squeak]

10:53.586 --> 10:55.497
[ Birds chirping ]

10:57.624 --> 11:00.537
All right, ladies,
we all know who you are.

11:00.527 --> 11:02.006
The rules state
we gotta take roll,

11:01.995 --> 11:03.201
so when Mike
calls your name,

11:03.196 --> 11:06.473
give me a "yeah,"
a "yo," or a "yum"

11:06.466 --> 11:08.309
- Sarah Mason.
- Yo.

11:08.635 --> 11:10.546
♪♪

11:12.672 --> 11:14.982
- Michelle Akila.
- Here.

11:15.275 --> 11:17.186
♪♪

11:17.944 --> 11:20.481
- Shannon Hastings.
- I'm here.

11:20.647 --> 11:22.558
♪♪

11:23.683 --> 11:26.391
- Samantha Pines.
- Right here as usual.

11:26.786 --> 11:28.697
♪♪

11:30.657 --> 11:33.365
Last but not least,
Anita Gunners.

11:33.359 --> 11:34.633
Yuppers.

11:34.827 --> 11:36.636
♪♪

11:38.164 --> 11:39.666
They're all present
and accounted for, sir.

11:39.666 --> 11:41.304
I told you this was
a piece of cake.

11:41.301 --> 11:42.302
All right, ladies,

11:42.302 --> 11:43.576
I know it's hot
and it's sticky

11:43.570 --> 11:45.174
and you'd rather
be anywhere else,

11:45.171 --> 11:46.582
but the warden wants
these stumps cleared

11:46.573 --> 11:48.348
by the end of the day.

11:48.341 --> 11:49.411
Understood?

11:49.409 --> 11:51.218
- I think we get it.
- Yeah, you want us

11:51.211 --> 11:53.521
to lay out, relax,
and catch some rays.

11:53.513 --> 11:55.652
See, ladies,
a tan'll look mighty nice

11:55.648 --> 11:57.321
at the lesbian
softball invitationals

11:57.483 --> 11:59.258
- next month.
- [ Scoffs ]

11:59.485 --> 12:00.691
Okay, joke time's over.

12:00.687 --> 12:04.157
Let's get these stumps cleared
by sundown.

12:04.157 --> 12:06.068
Water in the cooler,
and finger sandwiches

12:06.059 --> 12:07.504
will be served
promptly at 1:00.

12:07.493 --> 12:09.530
Here's one without the bread.

12:09.529 --> 12:11.668
And listen, if any of you
are thinking about

12:11.664 --> 12:13.541
pulling a Richard Kimble,
don't.

12:13.533 --> 12:16.343
The nearest 7-Eleven
is 50 miles away.

12:16.336 --> 12:17.781
It's not gonna be worth
that Slurpee.

12:17.770 --> 12:18.771
Oh, damn.

12:18.771 --> 12:20.409
I would kill
for those cola Slurpees

12:20.406 --> 12:21.714
just about now.

12:21.708 --> 12:24.587
I'm afraid killing's
the only option you've got.

12:24.577 --> 12:26.113
Don't tempt me.

12:26.112 --> 12:27.557
- Whatever.
- Ladies.

12:27.547 --> 12:28.890
Shovels are in the rear.

12:28.881 --> 12:31.589
Let's get it in motion.
Come on.

12:31.584 --> 12:33.257
- Whatever.
- I hate him.

12:33.253 --> 12:35.062
I hate slave labor.

12:35.255 --> 12:37.064
♪♪

13:54.334 --> 13:56.336
Hey, Mike,
you think it'll be all right

13:56.336 --> 13:58.612
if I took a moment alone
over by the stream?

13:58.604 --> 13:59.674
You know the rules, Pines.

13:59.672 --> 14:00.810
If I break 'em for you,

14:00.807 --> 14:02.343
gotta break 'em
for everybody else.

14:02.342 --> 14:03.446
- But--
- But what?

14:03.443 --> 14:05.047
Look.

14:05.044 --> 14:06.114
Ah, jeez.

14:06.112 --> 14:07.648
- What happened?
- I cut my arm

14:07.647 --> 14:09.320
on a beer bottle
some jerk litterbug

14:09.315 --> 14:10.726
tossed here ages ago.

14:10.717 --> 14:12.856
Come on.
Let me at least clean it out.

14:12.852 --> 14:14.889
Can't you wash it
right here?

14:14.887 --> 14:16.662
No.
It's muddy and disgusting.

14:16.656 --> 14:17.691
Come on, honey.

14:17.690 --> 14:18.828
I'll make it
worth your while

14:18.825 --> 14:20.327
back at holding tonight.

14:20.326 --> 14:21.828
All right, two minutes.

14:25.298 --> 14:27.505
Two minutes and counting,
baby.

14:35.508 --> 14:37.385
[ Birds chirping ]

14:41.047 --> 14:43.027
♪♪

15:07.240 --> 15:09.186
[ Water splashes ]

15:19.118 --> 15:21.029
[ Growling ]

15:21.721 --> 15:23.359
You gotta be kidding me.

15:24.757 --> 15:26.737
[ Screams ]

15:39.972 --> 15:41.815
Day's almost over, Mike.

15:41.808 --> 15:43.810
One more hour,
and we can take 'em home.

15:43.810 --> 15:45.084
Roger that, Carl.

15:48.614 --> 15:49.991
Hey, where's Sammy?

15:49.982 --> 15:51.427
Last I saw her,
she cut her arm

15:51.417 --> 15:52.418
with some glass.

15:52.418 --> 15:53.829
Yeah, it looked pretty bad.

15:53.820 --> 15:55.663
I thought she came back here
to the van for some first aid.

15:55.655 --> 15:57.965
Like they'd have anything more
than a 10-year-old Band-Aid.

15:57.957 --> 15:59.402
- So, where is she?
- Beats me.

15:59.392 --> 16:01.770
Maybe she took
an unscheduled vacation.

16:01.761 --> 16:02.739
Get my drift?

16:02.728 --> 16:03.934
That wouldn't be wise.

16:05.064 --> 16:06.907
- Where's Pines?
- She cut her arm.

16:06.899 --> 16:08.901
I sent her to you
to get it fixed.

16:08.901 --> 16:11.245
Well, she never showed.
You better go find her.

16:15.174 --> 16:17.484
Ladies, question.

16:17.477 --> 16:18.478
Where's Pines?

16:19.612 --> 16:20.818
All right, look,

16:20.813 --> 16:23.657
if you know something,
anything,

16:23.649 --> 16:24.753
it'd be better
if you tell me now

16:24.750 --> 16:25.751
before it goes any further.

16:25.751 --> 16:26.786
Understood?

16:27.787 --> 16:29.460
Okay, three words,

16:29.455 --> 16:31.332
guilt by association.

16:31.324 --> 16:32.530
You know
what the wardan's like.

16:32.525 --> 16:34.766
This will not go good
for any of us

16:34.760 --> 16:36.603
if Pines somehow gets away.

16:36.596 --> 16:38.166
Just a guess,
she was jonesing

16:38.164 --> 16:40.269
for a swim in that stream
over there all afternoon.

16:40.266 --> 16:41.609
Maybe she went skinny-dipping.

16:42.668 --> 16:44.841
Mike, she may be down
by the stream.

16:44.837 --> 16:45.975
- Go check it out.
- But--

16:45.972 --> 16:48.612
No "but," all right?
Just check it out now.

16:48.608 --> 16:49.552
Right.

16:51.110 --> 16:52.180
Let's just hope

16:52.178 --> 16:53.680
this is one
big misunderstanding.

16:57.850 --> 17:00.854
Hey, Carl, get down
to the stream quick.

17:00.853 --> 17:02.389
All right, ladies,
let's go see

17:02.388 --> 17:03.492
what Mike has found.

17:03.489 --> 17:04.866
After you, sir.

17:04.857 --> 17:08.327
On the contrary,
Ms. Gunners, after you.

17:08.327 --> 17:11.171
Arkansas manners
still apply here.

17:25.144 --> 17:26.417
Is that--

17:26.412 --> 17:27.685
Yeah, it's hers.

17:27.680 --> 17:29.216
So, what'd she do,
strip down and escape

17:29.215 --> 17:30.319
in her undies?

17:30.316 --> 17:31.693
Not if some accomplice
was waiting

17:31.684 --> 17:33.163
with a new wardrobe for her.

17:33.152 --> 17:34.256
That's not possible.

17:34.253 --> 17:35.596
One of us would have known.

17:35.588 --> 17:36.658
Yeah.

17:36.656 --> 17:38.033
Tough keeping secrets
in stir,

17:38.024 --> 17:39.094
especially an escape.

17:39.091 --> 17:40.331
How would someone
from the outside

17:40.326 --> 17:41.862
have known we were gonna
pull over right here?

17:41.861 --> 17:42.862
I didn't even know
where we were

17:42.862 --> 17:44.842
gonna stop till we got here.

17:44.830 --> 17:46.503
Nevertheless, she's gone.

17:46.499 --> 17:48.172
I gotta call this in
immediately.

17:48.167 --> 17:49.578
Mike,
take 'em back to the van.

17:49.569 --> 17:50.877
Keep 'em rounded up close.

17:50.870 --> 17:52.543
Yes, sir, boss.

17:52.538 --> 17:54.848
You heard the man, ladies.
Let's get moving.

17:54.840 --> 17:56.183
Michelle,
you're bleeding, girl.

17:56.175 --> 17:57.381
- What?
- Your arm

17:57.376 --> 17:59.583
- is covered in blood.
- How'd you get cut?

17:59.579 --> 18:02.287
It's not me bleeding,
hitches.

18:03.950 --> 18:07.227
It's this tree.
It's covered in blood.

18:13.059 --> 18:15.369
That's right, sir.
She just up and disappeared.

18:15.361 --> 18:16.567
Seems weird.

18:16.562 --> 18:18.633
Her sentence was up
the end of next month.

18:18.631 --> 18:19.803
That's right, Warden.

18:19.799 --> 18:22.143
Chopper's in the air
before we left the site.

18:22.134 --> 18:23.636
I'm sure we'll find her.

18:25.271 --> 18:27.410
Warden, I--

18:27.406 --> 18:29.716
Sir, are you there?

18:30.743 --> 18:32.051
Sir?

18:34.113 --> 18:35.751
Damn cell towers
ain't worth a damn.

18:35.748 --> 18:38.820
Yeah, I lost my bars
about ten miles back.

18:42.622 --> 18:44.101
Stop, and see if we can help.

18:44.090 --> 18:45.228
That's against regulations.

18:45.224 --> 18:46.294
Clearly states
that you're not--

18:46.292 --> 18:47.669
Give it a rest, will you?

18:49.395 --> 18:50.806
Stop the van.

18:59.271 --> 19:00.341
Do you need a doctor?

19:00.339 --> 19:01.511
Our cell phones are down,

19:01.507 --> 19:03.077
but we can take you
to the nearest hospital.

19:03.075 --> 19:04.611
Y'all might need
some looking after yourself,

19:04.610 --> 19:06.521
kind sirs.

19:08.648 --> 19:11.322
You, we can do this
one of two ways,

19:11.317 --> 19:12.796
slow and easy
or just plain dead.

19:12.785 --> 19:14.321
Your choice.

19:14.320 --> 19:15.799
Easy.

19:15.788 --> 19:17.529
We do it easy.
Just keep your cool.

19:17.523 --> 19:19.594
- We'll cooperate.
- Good.

19:19.592 --> 19:22.004
Hand over your guns.
Slowly.

19:29.168 --> 19:30.545
Good buy.

19:30.536 --> 19:31.810
Now, it's time
for all of us ladies

19:31.804 --> 19:33.784
- to mosey on out of here.
- Now, hold on there.

19:33.773 --> 19:35.650
You got something to say,
cowboy?

19:35.641 --> 19:37.484
No, nothing.
Nothing at all.

19:37.476 --> 19:38.978
I didn't think so.

19:38.978 --> 19:41.857
Now, open up the side door,
and let 'em all go.

19:41.847 --> 19:44.327
- Whoa there, dude.
- Easy, lady.

19:44.316 --> 19:46.728
- I'll do it from my side.
- Good idea.

19:50.489 --> 19:52.230
So long, suckers.

19:53.292 --> 19:55.829
Baby, you just rock my world.

19:55.828 --> 19:56.806
Hmm.

19:59.165 --> 20:00.667
This is seriously messed up.

20:00.666 --> 20:02.077
<i>It's the last thing I need.</i>

20:03.302 --> 20:06.044
Look, just stick close to me.
You'll be fine.

20:06.038 --> 20:08.177
To be continued, sweetheart.

20:08.174 --> 20:11.678
We're in the middle
of a felony here.

20:11.677 --> 20:12.849
Try that again, cop,

20:12.845 --> 20:14.984
and you'll be playing
pocket pool with no balls.

20:14.980 --> 20:17.586
Yeah, creep. My girl here
means what she says.

20:17.583 --> 20:18.891
All right, listen.

20:18.884 --> 20:20.488
Nobody wants to he
a hero here,

20:20.486 --> 20:21.556
right, Mike?

20:21.554 --> 20:23.261
- Right, sir.
- All right,

20:23.255 --> 20:25.360
let's just stay calm,
and we'll all get along.

20:25.357 --> 20:27.837
I don't know about
these two prom queens.

20:30.429 --> 20:31.669
I'm in.

20:31.664 --> 20:33.166
What do I do?

20:33.165 --> 20:34.838
Well, for now,
until they decide to join us,

20:34.834 --> 20:35.835
cover 'em.

20:35.835 --> 20:37.075
You two screws
back in the back

20:37.069 --> 20:39.515
with the regular folk.

20:39.672 --> 20:40.707
Now.

20:41.073 --> 20:42.950
[ Tires squeal ]

20:55.788 --> 20:58.735
Earth to Adam.
Come in, Adam.

20:58.724 --> 21:00.067
Over.

21:00.059 --> 21:01.595
Ah. I'm sorry.

21:03.195 --> 21:04.435
What you thinking 'bout?

21:04.430 --> 21:06.068
How impressed you are
with my detective skills?

21:06.065 --> 21:09.444
Nah, not exactly, no.
1..

21:09.435 --> 21:11.210
Just thinking about that scene
back there, you know?

21:11.203 --> 21:12.807
I... I don't really know

21:12.805 --> 21:14.716
if I'm cut out
for this kind of work.

21:14.707 --> 21:17.153
Hey, I felt the same way
when I first started.

21:17.143 --> 21:18.622
No joke.

21:19.779 --> 21:22.385
- You just gotta do what I do.
- What's that?

21:22.381 --> 21:24.588
Whenever you want a break
from the job,

21:24.583 --> 21:27.462
- just crank up the tunes.
[ ♪♪ ]

21:27.453 --> 21:29.592
This? This is what you do
to unwind?

21:29.588 --> 21:30.760
This is what you like
to listen to?

21:30.756 --> 21:31.826
What's that
supposed to mean?

21:31.824 --> 21:32.802
What do you like listening to,

21:32.792 --> 21:35.796
that techno music,
some disco?

21:35.795 --> 21:37.001
Terrible.

21:37.229 --> 21:38.731
[ Radio station changes ]

21:38.931 --> 21:40.069
Reporter:
So, be on the lookout

21:40.065 --> 21:41.942
for these
four female escapees

21:41.934 --> 21:43.345
and their driver.

21:43.335 --> 21:44.973
Once again,
these women escaped

21:44.970 --> 21:46.278
from custody earlier today

21:46.272 --> 21:47.683
and should be
considered armed

21:47.673 --> 21:49.448
and extremely dangerous.

21:49.608 --> 21:51.781
If you encounter them,
call your local law enforce--

21:52.011 --> 21:53.012
[ Radio station changes ]

21:53.279 --> 21:55.156
So much for getting
your mind off it.

21:55.147 --> 21:57.457
Looks like our laundry list
just got longer.

21:58.818 --> 22:00.820
♪♪

22:01.086 --> 22:03.293
[ Bugs chirping ]

22:14.333 --> 22:15.437
Ladies and gentlemen,

22:15.434 --> 22:17.380
I'd like to welcome you
nice people

22:17.369 --> 22:18.473
on this nonstop service

22:18.470 --> 22:20.177
from the big house
to freedom.

22:20.172 --> 22:21.276
We'll be going at the speed

22:21.273 --> 22:22.377
of whatever
Captain Honey here

22:22.374 --> 22:23.717
damn well pleases,

22:23.709 --> 22:25.620
so at this time,
I'd like to invite you

22:25.611 --> 22:27.716
to fasten your seat belts
and make sure your tray tables

22:27.713 --> 22:29.021
and seat backs
are in their full

22:29.014 --> 22:30.618
upright position.

22:30.616 --> 22:32.152
Lastly, if anyone decides
to get cute

22:32.151 --> 22:33.630
or do anything stupid,

22:33.619 --> 22:36.293
I will gladly
blow your heads off.

22:40.326 --> 22:41.964
They got
some surveillance cameras

22:41.961 --> 22:43.668
a couple miles up
where Route 40 crosses.

22:43.662 --> 22:45.972
Maybe we can attract
some attention.

22:45.965 --> 22:48.912
Do what, dance?
Tell jokes?

22:55.140 --> 22:56.983
Now what?

22:56.976 --> 22:59.081
So much for our act
for the cameras.

23:02.882 --> 23:04.520
So, where the hell
is she going?

23:04.516 --> 23:05.995
Who the hell knows?

23:07.553 --> 23:10.227
Excuse me. Excuse me.

23:10.222 --> 23:11.701
This is my stop.

23:11.690 --> 23:13.192
Just hold your water, babe.

23:13.192 --> 23:15.536
It'll be everyone's stop
in just about two minutes.

23:32.244 --> 23:34.087
[ Engine shuts off]

23:37.616 --> 23:39.357
Okay, baby,
get everybody out.

23:43.689 --> 23:45.191
Out, out. Everybody out.

23:45.190 --> 23:46.692
Move, move.

23:46.692 --> 23:48.262
Move it. Get over there.

23:48.260 --> 23:50.536
Get over there. Move.

23:58.437 --> 23:59.438
What now?

23:59.438 --> 24:01.213
What's wrong with you,
princess?

24:01.206 --> 24:02.446
I'll tell you what's wrong.

24:02.441 --> 24:03.476
I got six months left,

24:03.475 --> 24:05.386
and you just tacked on
ten easy.

24:05.377 --> 24:07.323
Give it a rest, dragon lady.

24:07.313 --> 24:08.621
What do you got
waiting for you

24:08.614 --> 24:10.457
when you get out, anyway?

24:10.449 --> 24:12.326
My boy.

24:13.986 --> 24:15.659
Got a little boy.

24:15.654 --> 24:18.658
Okay, ladies, strip.

24:18.657 --> 24:20.500
Get rid of what
you're wearing.

24:20.492 --> 24:23.769
- Even me?
- Yeah, sweetheart, even you.

24:23.762 --> 24:25.173
Here. Put this on.

24:26.498 --> 24:28.068
[Sighs]

24:30.302 --> 24:32.248
You ain't got nothing
we haven't seen, girl.

24:32.237 --> 24:34.183
- Do it.
- You first.

24:34.173 --> 24:36.449
Hey, if you feeling froggy,
you might as well jump.

24:36.442 --> 24:39.616
Come on, soy sauce,
make your move.

24:39.611 --> 24:41.454
I told you.

24:41.447 --> 24:42.983
I'm gonna rip your eyes out.

24:42.982 --> 24:44.757
You don't--

24:44.750 --> 24:46.286
You know what?

24:46.285 --> 24:47.696
Get your hands off me.

24:50.122 --> 24:52.193
- Enough.
- How you like that, huh?

24:52.458 --> 24:54.438
♪♪

24:54.960 --> 24:56.030
- Off me.
- Get off me.

24:56.028 --> 24:57.473
Honey, he's getting away.

24:57.463 --> 24:59.875
Oh, no, he's not.
Cover the old fart.

24:59.865 --> 25:02.038
- Got it.
- Keep your hands off my head.

25:02.768 --> 25:05.305
[Girls hitting and groaning ]

25:05.504 --> 25:07.450
I ain't going anywhere.

25:10.876 --> 25:12.287
Damn you.

25:16.849 --> 25:18.795
[ Gunshots ]

25:21.453 --> 25:23.296
I think your boy
just bought it.

25:47.479 --> 25:49.720
- [ Gunshot]
- [Screams]

25:54.853 --> 25:56.526
You didn't think
you could outrun old Honey,

25:56.522 --> 25:57.728
now, did you?

25:59.691 --> 26:01.568
[Groans]

26:08.734 --> 26:10.008
[Sighs]

26:10.235 --> 26:12.112
Crap on a cracker.

26:17.342 --> 26:19.253
[ Labored breathing ]

26:33.258 --> 26:34.430
Where are they?

26:34.426 --> 26:35.803
I got 'em waiting
in the other van.

26:35.794 --> 26:38.468
- Did you get him?
- I got him.

26:39.898 --> 26:41.070
I just hope you don't have

26:41.066 --> 26:44.104
any of the same stupid ideas
your friend had.

26:44.103 --> 26:46.777
No, not at all.

26:46.772 --> 26:47.978
Good.

26:47.973 --> 26:50.419
Let's get the hell
out of here.

26:53.045 --> 26:55.616
[ Engine revs ]

26:58.717 --> 27:00.287
[ Bugs chirping ]

27:00.452 --> 27:01.556
Water.

27:07.259 --> 27:08.329
Water.

27:12.664 --> 27:14.644
[ Hatch squeaks open ]

27:17.402 --> 27:19.177
Water.

27:19.171 --> 27:20.775
Thank God.

27:22.441 --> 27:24.352
[Water dripping ]

28:13.192 --> 28:15.138
[Water sloshing ]

28:20.699 --> 28:22.303
Ah, yeah.

28:22.301 --> 28:23.575
Oh, yeah.

28:41.587 --> 28:43.260
[ Growl ]

29:02.107 --> 29:04.383
I hope this baby
has four-wheel drive.

29:04.376 --> 29:05.684
Why is that, Screw?

29:05.677 --> 29:07.953
This is the old road
to Wrightson Swamp,

29:07.946 --> 29:10.051
gets pretty mucky
the further you get in.

29:10.048 --> 29:12.528
We'll just see about that.

29:12.517 --> 29:14.360
Honey, did you hear
what he just said?

29:14.353 --> 29:15.388
What's that?

29:15.387 --> 29:16.730
That we're headed
into the swamp.

29:16.722 --> 29:17.757
Yeah, I heard that
from the guy

29:17.756 --> 29:19.099
who rented me the place.

29:19.091 --> 29:20.866
- What place?
- You'll see.

29:20.859 --> 29:22.270
It's only a few more miles.

29:22.261 --> 29:24.298
Sure as hell hope
this place of yours

29:24.296 --> 29:25.707
has indoor plumbing.

29:25.697 --> 29:26.903
As a matter of fact,

29:26.898 --> 29:29.401
the old man said it
was pretty well-equipped.

29:29.401 --> 29:30.971
- What old man?
- Don't worry, baby.

29:30.969 --> 29:32.380
He won't be talking
to anyone.

29:32.371 --> 29:33.611
How's that?

29:33.605 --> 29:36.415
Let's just say I pushed him
into early retirement.

29:36.408 --> 29:37.614
Aha.

29:40.412 --> 29:42.392
[ Bugs chirping ]

29:47.452 --> 29:48.795
[ Engine shuts off]

29:54.893 --> 29:57.499
Hell, it's even nicer
than I expected.

29:57.496 --> 29:59.100
It's even got a hot tub.

29:59.097 --> 30:01.134
Excuse me, but what the hell
are we doing here?

30:01.133 --> 30:03.135
You know, for someone enjoying
a little taste of freedom,

30:03.135 --> 30:04.637
you sure got a hell
of a mouth on you, girl.

30:04.636 --> 30:07.310
So I've been told,
but answer the question.

30:07.306 --> 30:09.081
Just chill. Chill.

30:09.074 --> 30:10.519
We're gonna settle in here

30:10.509 --> 30:12.989
- and just wait.
- Wait for what?

30:12.978 --> 30:14.980
Cops?
Bloodhounds? Choppers?

30:14.980 --> 30:16.459
- Et cetera, et cetera?
- Yeah, yeah.

30:16.448 --> 30:17.825
Something like that.

30:17.816 --> 30:19.318
Nah, this is gonna he

30:19.318 --> 30:21.320
our little home away
from home.

30:21.320 --> 30:23.095
Ladies,
pardon your delusion,

30:23.088 --> 30:24.158
but this is the first door

30:24.156 --> 30:25.464
they're gonna come
knocking on.

30:25.457 --> 30:26.663
- Trust me.
- She's right.

30:26.658 --> 30:28.160
This is absolute B.S.

30:28.160 --> 30:29.639
All you crazy bitches
are gonna do

30:29.628 --> 30:32.871
is get more time for us
or worse yet, get us killed.

30:32.864 --> 30:34.673
I want out, now.

30:34.666 --> 30:36.373
You ain't going nowhere,
bitch.

30:36.601 --> 30:38.444
<i>' [ Punch ]
' [ Groan ]</i>

30:38.637 --> 30:41.777
I'd think twice about
doing that again, sweetie.

30:41.773 --> 30:43.446
Next time, I might get mad.

30:43.442 --> 30:45.149
Soy sauce.

30:45.143 --> 30:47.555
You are here,
and you are going to stay here

30:47.546 --> 30:48.490
with the rest of us

30:48.480 --> 30:50.289
until I say different,
understand?

30:50.282 --> 30:53.661
Yeah, I get it,
but I don't gotta like it.

30:53.652 --> 30:55.654
That's all I'm asking for,
really.

30:55.654 --> 30:57.964
You got anything else to say,
sweetness?

30:57.956 --> 30:59.663
- Yeah, one thing.
- And what's that?

30:59.658 --> 31:01.331
Don't go to sleep.

31:01.326 --> 31:04.466
All right,
everybody get in the house.

31:07.532 --> 31:09.375
Make sure the man here
is tied up good.

31:09.368 --> 31:11.075
He's our insurance policy.

31:11.069 --> 31:12.571
You got it, baby.

31:12.571 --> 31:14.312
And by the way,

31:14.306 --> 31:16.081
thanks for earlier.

31:16.074 --> 31:17.553
Don't mention it.

31:22.581 --> 31:24.219
You, out.

31:24.483 --> 31:26.429
[ Thunder ]

31:28.353 --> 31:30.264
[ Rain ]

31:30.522 --> 31:32.365
[Siren ]

31:35.394 --> 31:36.737
Boss.

31:38.663 --> 31:40.267
Here you go.
It's still hot, I think.

31:41.533 --> 31:42.739
Thanks, kid.

31:42.734 --> 31:44.407
Yeah, might be
a little watered down, though.

31:44.403 --> 31:47.350
- I couldn't find a lid.
- Cop coffee.

31:47.339 --> 31:49.410
It's supposed
to he watered down.

31:49.408 --> 31:51.752
- I think it's in the bylaws.
- Right.

31:51.743 --> 31:53.120
Did you hear anything
from the hospital

31:53.111 --> 31:54.852
- about the call today?
- Yeah.

31:54.846 --> 31:55.881
I talked to the doctor.

31:55.881 --> 31:57.189
He says the guy's
still in shock.

31:57.182 --> 31:58.593
He keeps raving
about his buddy

31:58.583 --> 32:00.358
being eaten by a shark.

32:00.352 --> 32:02.696
Well, after what we saw,
I kind of half believe him.

32:02.687 --> 32:04.758
Yeah, right. What about you?
You find anything?

32:05.757 --> 32:07.395
What is that, evidence?

32:07.392 --> 32:09.429
No,
but don't you just love it?

32:09.428 --> 32:11.567
It's a vintage
Coca-Cola bottle,

32:11.563 --> 32:13.236
solid glass,

32:13.231 --> 32:16.371
not like this plastic and cans
we have today.

32:16.368 --> 32:17.540
It must have been
lying around here

32:17.536 --> 32:18.742
for 80 years.

32:18.737 --> 32:21.047
Now, mind you,
it needs a little work,

32:21.039 --> 32:22.074
but once it's polished up,

32:22.073 --> 32:24.212
it's gonna look great
in my minibar.

32:24.209 --> 32:26.780
- I meant about the case.
- I know what you meant.

32:26.778 --> 32:27.813
Take a look around.

32:27.813 --> 32:28.917
It's pretty obvious

32:28.914 --> 32:30.791
this is where
they changed vehicles.

32:30.782 --> 32:32.989
Yeah,
but what make and model?

32:32.984 --> 32:34.622
I don't know.
Something big.

32:34.619 --> 32:36.656
The warden said
one prisoner escaped.

32:36.655 --> 32:38.396
That still leaves
six more passengers

32:38.390 --> 32:39.596
to cart around.

32:39.591 --> 32:40.934
- True.
- Let's get on the horn

32:40.926 --> 32:42.803
to all
the rental car companies

32:42.794 --> 32:44.671
within a 50-mile radius,

32:44.663 --> 32:45.733
see what
they've got on the road

32:45.730 --> 32:46.731
that meets our criteria.

32:46.731 --> 32:47.801
I don't know.

32:47.799 --> 32:48.800
I think most of those places

32:48.800 --> 32:50.177
are gonna be closed now,
don't you think?

32:50.168 --> 32:52.910
Let's go wake 'em up.

32:52.904 --> 32:54.247
All right.

32:54.439 --> 32:56.282
[ Thunder ]

33:07.118 --> 33:08.290
Now stay put,

33:08.286 --> 33:09.788
and you might just make it
through the night.

33:09.788 --> 33:11.529
Yeah,
like that's gonna happen.

33:11.523 --> 33:12.934
Your girlfriend'll
put a slug in me

33:12.924 --> 33:14.460
the moment
I'm no use to you.

33:14.459 --> 33:15.631
- That's not true.
- Yeah?

33:15.627 --> 33:17.300
Then who made
Samantha disappear?

33:17.295 --> 33:18.672
It was her, right?

33:18.663 --> 33:19.937
She knocked off Pines

33:19.931 --> 33:22.605
to put us on the road
before nightfall, right?

33:22.601 --> 33:24.547
You're crazy.
She's not like that.

33:24.536 --> 33:26.880
Yeah.
Tell that to Mike.

33:26.872 --> 33:29.944
Just shut up,
or I'll kill you myself.

33:29.941 --> 33:30.976
So, what now?

33:30.976 --> 33:34.048
I've been in stir
for five years.

33:34.045 --> 33:35.023
I'm gonna go slip

33:35.013 --> 33:36.959
into something
more comfortable.

33:39.117 --> 33:41.063
[ Grunts ]

33:41.286 --> 33:42.788
[ Thunder ]

33:42.988 --> 33:44.695
I hate the rain.

33:44.689 --> 33:46.191
Really?
I kind of like it.

33:46.191 --> 33:47.727
Sounds like a...

33:47.726 --> 33:49.728
like an atmosphere
or something.

33:49.728 --> 33:51.366
So better than the cell block,
isn't it?

33:51.363 --> 33:54.640
It's the same thing.
We're trapped here.

33:54.633 --> 33:55.873
Prison's a prison.

33:55.867 --> 33:57.972
Suit yourself,
but I'm gonna make

33:57.969 --> 33:59.175
the best of it.

33:59.170 --> 34:01.172
Well, I know how
you could start.

34:01.172 --> 34:03.413
How 'bout a hot bath
before we go to bed?

34:03.408 --> 34:05.012
Now, that sounds
like a good idea.

34:05.010 --> 34:06.717
I haven't had one of those
in so long.

34:06.711 --> 34:07.815
Where is it?

34:07.812 --> 34:09.518
Second bathroom
down the hall.

34:09.514 --> 34:10.891
I turned it on
the minute we got here.

34:10.882 --> 34:12.384
Should be coming to a boil
just about now.

34:12.384 --> 34:14.659
Sounds good.
I'm game.

34:14.652 --> 34:16.360
How 'bout you, Sarah?

34:16.353 --> 34:17.856
No, you guys go ahead.

34:17.856 --> 34:19.358
I'll meet you
in a few minutes.

34:19.357 --> 34:21.199
Suit yourself.

34:27.431 --> 34:29.411
[ Fire crackling ]

34:52.223 --> 34:53.725
Anything good?

34:53.725 --> 34:56.069
Yeah, actually.

34:56.061 --> 34:58.302
I just found
this first-edition copy

34:58.296 --> 35:01.368
of Charles Dickens'
"A Tale of Two Cities."

35:01.533 --> 35:03.638
Yeah, so?

35:03.635 --> 35:06.616
You've heard of it, right?

35:06.605 --> 35:09.279
You actually read books?

35:09.274 --> 35:13.051
In prison, there ain't nothing
better to do.

35:14.980 --> 35:16.323
Let me see that.

35:18.650 --> 35:21.893
"It was the best of times.
It was the worst of times."

35:21.886 --> 35:24.492
Honey, I don't want nothing

35:24.489 --> 35:26.901
but good times
from here on in.

35:26.891 --> 35:27.926
I know, hut--

35:27.926 --> 35:30.930
I've had enough
of the bad times.

35:30.929 --> 35:34.069
I know, baby.
I know.

35:46.745 --> 35:48.691
[ Thunder ]

35:50.415 --> 35:52.088
[Sighs]

35:52.283 --> 35:53.921
Where the hell is she,
for God's sake?

35:53.918 --> 35:56.660
Relax.
Enjoy her not being here.

35:56.655 --> 35:59.135
Sharon, you know
we have to get out of here

35:59.124 --> 36:00.535
more sooner than later,
right?

36:00.792 --> 36:03.102
<i>- You think it's gonna get bad?
- Girl,</i>

36:03.294 --> 36:05.137
I've been smelling bad crap
all my life,

36:05.130 --> 36:07.610
and this is the limburger
of bad.

36:07.599 --> 36:09.101
I know what you mean.

36:09.100 --> 36:10.135
Yeah, you do.

36:10.135 --> 36:11.375
Someone does
something stupid,

36:11.369 --> 36:12.439
a gun goes off,

36:12.437 --> 36:14.348
and we're all
accessories to murder.

36:14.339 --> 36:16.979
I got a kid back home.
I can't go back to the joint.

36:16.975 --> 36:18.147
I know.

36:18.343 --> 36:20.220
[ Rain ]

36:20.945 --> 36:23.482
<i>- Hey, guys. What'd I miss?
- Not a thing, girl.</i>

36:23.481 --> 36:24.824
Michelle and I
were just talking

36:24.816 --> 36:26.693
about our recent benefactors.

36:26.685 --> 36:29.188
Yeah, they are kind of harsh.

36:29.187 --> 36:32.327
Harsh? Heh. Nice word.
Love it.

36:32.323 --> 36:33.802
They did get us out.

36:33.792 --> 36:35.294
Get us out to where,

36:35.293 --> 36:37.705
some "Friday the 13th" cabin
in the woods?

36:37.696 --> 36:39.733
Yeah, this is not my idea
of getting us out.

36:39.731 --> 36:41.335
Look,
tomorrow they'll most likely

36:41.332 --> 36:42.572
go their separate ways.

36:42.567 --> 36:44.979
Then you'll have the option
to either give up

36:44.969 --> 36:46.676
or take off running.

36:46.671 --> 36:48.309
You're forgetting
the third option.

36:48.306 --> 36:49.376
Yeah, what's that?

36:49.374 --> 36:51.149
They shoot us all
to keep us from talking.

36:51.142 --> 36:53.486
Bad option, very bad.

36:53.478 --> 36:55.219
You think
they'd go that far?

36:55.213 --> 36:56.851
"Do you think
they'd go that far?"

36:56.848 --> 36:58.020
Do you remember
what they just did

36:58.016 --> 37:00.428
to Mike a couple hours ago?

37:02.353 --> 37:04.026
Yeah. You got
a point there, girl.

37:04.022 --> 37:06.161
Yeah, I most certainly do.

37:08.359 --> 37:10.339
[Sighs]

37:10.528 --> 37:12.235
[ Thunder ]

37:17.102 --> 37:19.048
[ Birds chirping ]

37:31.750 --> 37:32.888
Yes.

37:47.232 --> 37:49.234
[ Yawning ]

37:50.869 --> 37:51.904
If you don't mind,

37:51.903 --> 37:53.712
I could really use
a bathroom break.

37:53.705 --> 37:57.118
You, untie him,
and watch him unload.

37:57.108 --> 37:58.314
What'd you say to me?

37:58.309 --> 37:59.652
"Untie him--"

37:59.644 --> 38:01.385
No,
I heard what you said first.

38:01.379 --> 38:02.722
What came after that?

38:04.949 --> 38:07.259
Egg roll,
either you watch him poop,

38:07.252 --> 38:08.322
or you watch him
poop his pants.

38:08.319 --> 38:09.423
Your choice.

38:13.258 --> 38:14.293
If it's any consolation,

38:14.292 --> 38:16.101
it's not a lat of fun
for me either.

38:16.094 --> 38:19.405
Yeah, it better not be.
I'll tell you that.

38:19.397 --> 38:21.673
This may take a while.
I have prostate issues.

38:21.966 --> 38:24.003
[Sighs]

38:24.269 --> 38:27.011
Lord, what did I do
to deserve this?

38:28.773 --> 38:31.413
[ Birds chirping ]

39:03.708 --> 39:05.654
[ Water rushing ]

39:17.488 --> 39:19.490
[Sighs]

39:23.127 --> 39:25.073
[Water splashing ]

39:30.235 --> 39:31.680
[ Humming ]

39:32.871 --> 39:34.873
[ Shark makes noise ]

39:35.073 --> 39:36.916
[Stops humming ]

39:38.743 --> 39:40.689
[ Gasps ]

39:46.551 --> 39:48.531
[ Low growl ]

39:55.093 --> 39:57.073
[ Earth crumbling ]

39:58.930 --> 40:01.103
Help. Oh, my God.

40:04.669 --> 40:06.615
[ Screams ]

40:11.175 --> 40:13.121
[ Birds chirping ]

40:13.912 --> 40:15.858
[ Horn hanks ]

40:17.015 --> 40:18.119
Yes, sir,
we're looking into it

40:18.116 --> 40:19.220
right now.

40:19.217 --> 40:21.254
Yes, he is.

40:21.252 --> 40:23.732
I'll let you know
as soon as I hear something.

40:23.721 --> 40:26.224
Of course. Okay.

40:26.224 --> 40:28.465
Give it to me, Chin.
What you got?

40:28.459 --> 40:29.597
Chin?

40:29.594 --> 40:31.198
Obscure reference.
Never mind.

40:31.195 --> 40:32.196
What'd he say?

40:32.196 --> 40:33.937
Well, turns out
you were right.

40:33.932 --> 40:36.139
The guy inside says
he rented a minivan

40:36.134 --> 40:37.272
to a lady
using a stolen credit card

40:37.268 --> 40:38.713
yesterday morning.

40:38.703 --> 40:40.444
And they decided to keep it
secret till this morning?

40:40.438 --> 40:41.542
Well, the card
only got flagged

40:41.539 --> 40:42.609
late last night

40:42.607 --> 40:43.984
after the place
had already closed, so...

40:43.975 --> 40:46.956
Let me guess.
White minivan.

40:46.945 --> 40:48.253
Yeah. How'd you know?

40:48.246 --> 40:50.590
It's the most popular color
in rental car ﬂeets,

40:50.581 --> 40:53.391
followed by black,
off-white, and beige.

40:53.384 --> 40:54.624
You're good, boss.

40:54.619 --> 40:56.724
- You're real good.
- That's what they tell me.

40:56.721 --> 40:58.598
Listen, now we actually caught
a lucky break.

40:58.589 --> 41:00.569
There's two blue stripes
running down the side of it.

41:00.558 --> 41:02.469
Excellent.
You get the plate?

41:02.460 --> 41:03.598
Already up
on the comm lines.

41:03.594 --> 41:04.629
And by any chance,

41:04.629 --> 41:06.734
is there LoJack
on any of these vehicles?

41:06.731 --> 41:08.074
I don't think so.

41:08.066 --> 41:10.740
Mm. How 'bout a description
of the woman?

41:10.735 --> 41:12.840
Well, the guy inside said
she was a real looker,

41:12.837 --> 41:14.009
had red hair.

41:14.005 --> 41:17.111
Hmm. That's helpful.
You pull the videotape?

41:17.108 --> 41:18.815
- Nothing.
- What do you mean, "nothing"?

41:18.810 --> 41:20.187
Well, they have
two video cameras,

41:20.178 --> 41:21.521
but both of them are fake.

41:21.512 --> 41:22.616
Well, that'll teach 'em.

41:22.613 --> 41:25.093
Yeah.
So, where to new?

41:25.083 --> 41:26.994
I'm hungry. Lunch.

41:26.985 --> 41:28.157
Good idea.

41:28.353 --> 41:30.196
[ Engine rumbles]

41:38.296 --> 41:39.274
Here we are.

41:39.263 --> 41:41.334
Peaches and beans,
my specialty.

41:41.332 --> 41:43.608
- Breakfast is served.
- Oh, no, I'm good.

41:43.601 --> 41:46.343
I just got a heaping helping
of Carl's peaches and beans,

41:46.337 --> 41:47.816
and I'm done.

41:47.805 --> 41:50.479
- Sorry.
- Yeah, I bet you are,

41:50.475 --> 41:51.510
Spungebob Brownpants.

41:51.509 --> 41:53.386
Tie him up again.

41:53.378 --> 41:55.221
He's an old man.
He's not going anywhere.

41:55.213 --> 41:56.556
Just let him sit here.

41:56.547 --> 41:58.527
I said tie him up.

41:58.516 --> 41:59.995
Why don't you tie him up?

41:59.984 --> 42:02.123
I'm gonna go
have a cigarette.

42:02.120 --> 42:04.157
Hey, hey.
Just wait a hot second here.

42:04.155 --> 42:06.396
I'm tired of waiting.

42:07.458 --> 42:09.836
So, can I interest anyone?

42:10.862 --> 42:12.864
[ Birds chirping ]

42:13.698 --> 42:15.678
[ Flicks lighter ]

42:20.004 --> 42:22.143
<i>[ Gasps]
Sarah.</i>

42:23.241 --> 42:24.379
Everybody.

42:24.375 --> 42:26.855
- Oh, no. Sarah.
- What's going on?

42:26.844 --> 42:29.017
Something's happened to her.
Come on. Hurry.

42:31.549 --> 42:32.653
[ Gasps ]

42:35.219 --> 42:36.254
What happened?

42:36.254 --> 42:38.495
I don't know,
but she's dead.

42:38.489 --> 42:41.197
Looks like she fell
into a wood chipper.

42:41.192 --> 42:42.899
Come on. We better go
take a look around.

42:42.894 --> 42:45.500
That is so not a good idea
right now.

42:45.496 --> 42:46.736
But we're doing it anyway.

42:46.731 --> 42:49.371
- Even him?
- Him most of all.

42:49.367 --> 42:50.778
Come on.

42:50.768 --> 42:52.406
Okay, move it.

42:56.841 --> 42:58.787
[ Bugs buzzing ]

42:59.510 --> 43:01.456
♪♪

43:02.213 --> 43:04.284
Here. Over here.

43:09.420 --> 43:10.865
Oh, my God.

43:12.356 --> 43:15.735
That was no wood chipper.

43:15.726 --> 43:17.569
This is a tooth.

43:17.562 --> 43:20.441
Not just a tooth.
That's a shark tooth...

43:20.431 --> 43:22.035
like this.

43:23.634 --> 43:25.910
But then
what happened to her?

43:25.903 --> 43:27.610
Yeah, there ain't no sharks
in these woods.

43:27.605 --> 43:28.982
Yeah, not that we know of.

43:28.973 --> 43:30.077
How do you know
there ain't one

43:30.074 --> 43:32.054
swimming in that stream
over there?

43:32.043 --> 43:33.113
Last time I saws "Jaws,"

43:33.111 --> 43:35.057
they were limited
to salt water.

43:35.046 --> 43:37.583
Plus, when she crawled in,
she was hone-dry.

43:37.582 --> 43:41.086
Those ruts over there,
they were made recently.

43:41.085 --> 43:43.998
Whatever killed Sarah
made them.

43:43.988 --> 43:45.490
What kind of creature
does that?

43:45.490 --> 43:48.471
Honey, have you got an idea?

43:49.760 --> 43:51.797
Not a clue,

43:51.796 --> 43:54.902
but we got a body to bury,
ladies.

44:05.610 --> 44:07.180
You want to tell me
how she ended up here

44:07.178 --> 44:08.623
with this sticking
out of her leg?

44:08.613 --> 44:09.683
I don't know.

44:09.680 --> 44:11.091
Maybe it was
just laying on the ground

44:11.082 --> 44:12.493
for some strange reason.

44:12.483 --> 44:14.622
Yeah, it could be
a fossil or something.

44:14.619 --> 44:15.825
It's a shark's tooth.

44:15.820 --> 44:18.266
It's some kind of mutation,
a monster.

44:18.256 --> 44:20.031
Oh, it's a monster,
all right.

44:20.024 --> 44:21.503
Hold it right there, buddy.

44:21.492 --> 44:24.302
Whoa, nice to meet you, too.
Put that away.

44:25.429 --> 44:26.430
Or don't.

44:26.430 --> 44:28.808
What the hell
are you two doing here?

44:28.799 --> 44:30.107
Ah, we're waiting
on the next bus

44:30.101 --> 44:31.273
out of the swamp.

44:31.269 --> 44:33.180
Why?
What happened to your ride?

44:33.171 --> 44:34.946
- It was eaten.
- Eaten?

44:34.939 --> 44:36.509
Eaten by a monstrous
prehistoric shark.

44:36.507 --> 44:39.317
- Oh, my God.
- We gotta get out of here.

44:39.310 --> 44:41.187
Sorry, ladies, but our van
is staying put right here,

44:41.179 --> 44:42.283
and so are you.

44:42.280 --> 44:43.691
You two, come along.

44:43.681 --> 44:44.716
- You got this?
- Yeah.

44:44.715 --> 44:45.785
They're kidnapping us.

44:45.983 --> 44:47.792
I know,
but look at that rack.

44:48.953 --> 44:51.832
What were you two
really doing out there?

44:51.822 --> 44:53.824
Hold on. I got a question
for you first.

44:53.824 --> 44:55.565
Do you know of anyone
doing any blasting

44:55.560 --> 44:56.698
or drilling in the area?

44:56.694 --> 44:59.675
We're not from around here.
Don't know.

44:59.664 --> 45:01.666
All right, look,
I'm a geologist.

45:01.666 --> 45:02.667
John here is my assistant.

45:02.667 --> 45:04.374
We're here
to monitor vibrations.

45:04.368 --> 45:05.642
What kind of vibrations?

45:05.636 --> 45:08.173
What, like good vibrations,
like the song?

45:08.172 --> 45:10.083
Bad vibrations, actually.

45:10.074 --> 45:12.714
Yeah, about two weeks ago,
Delgado Petroleum

45:12.710 --> 45:14.348
started fracking
some old wells in the area.

45:14.345 --> 45:16.018
What the hell's farking?

45:16.013 --> 45:18.493
Fracking. It's short
for hydraulic fracturing,

45:18.482 --> 45:20.519
and it seems like Delgado
may have gone too far

45:20.518 --> 45:22.725
and completely shattered
the subterranean shale bed.

45:22.720 --> 45:24.825
Mister, all I just heard
was blah-blah- blah.

45:24.822 --> 45:26.233
Now, you start making sense

45:26.224 --> 45:29.034
before my trigger finger
gets itchy.

45:29.026 --> 45:31.870
Hold on a second.
Look, in 2007,

45:31.862 --> 45:33.170
scientists discovered
an ocean

45:33.164 --> 45:36.077
lying 1,400 kilometers
below eastern Asia

45:36.067 --> 45:38.172
about the size of Texas.

45:38.169 --> 45:40.513
Now, if I was a betting man,
and I am,

45:40.504 --> 45:42.347
I would say
the good old U.S. of A.

45:42.340 --> 45:43.785
Has an underground ocean
of its own.

45:43.774 --> 45:45.048
What the hell
does that have to do

45:45.042 --> 45:47.682
with what happened to Sarah
and your van?

45:47.678 --> 45:50.181
Oceans are teeming with life,

45:50.181 --> 45:52.889
including predators
like sharks.

45:52.883 --> 45:55.193
Now, my fear is that Delgado
may have inadvertently

45:55.186 --> 45:57.530
opened a superhighway
between the Earth's surface

45:57.521 --> 45:59.364
and one of these vast
underground waterways.

45:59.357 --> 46:00.734
And while
Delgado's greasing palms

46:00.725 --> 46:02.068
in Little Rock
and Washington,

46:02.059 --> 46:03.094
we might be facing

46:03.094 --> 46:04.368
a prehistoric monster
we haven't seen

46:04.362 --> 46:06.035
in about 40 million years.

46:06.030 --> 46:08.909
A sharkasaurus
13 to 20 feet long,

46:08.899 --> 46:10.810
and a natural-born
killing machine,

46:10.801 --> 46:13.372
both in water and on land.

46:13.371 --> 46:14.315
On land?

46:14.305 --> 46:15.807
And believe me when I say

46:15.806 --> 46:17.649
this is definitely not
a fossil.

46:17.642 --> 46:20.748
Crap on a cracker.
Everybody listen up.

46:20.745 --> 46:22.725
We are getting the hell
out of here right now.

46:22.713 --> 46:23.919
- Hallelujah.
- But how?

46:23.914 --> 46:26.087
That creature may be out there
waiting for us.

46:26.083 --> 46:28.927
We'll figure a way.
Pack your stuff.

46:39.163 --> 46:41.905
Shannon:
You think we can make it?

46:41.899 --> 46:43.742
Who can tell?

46:43.734 --> 46:45.407
I say we risk it.

46:45.403 --> 46:47.007
It's only 100 sweet yards
to that van.

46:47.004 --> 46:48.745
Then by all means,
chopstick, lead the way.

46:48.739 --> 46:51.083
Here's the keys.
We're right behind you.

47:17.835 --> 47:19.178
Well, what's the matter,
Tokyo Rose?

47:19.170 --> 47:20.808
Thought you were willing
to risk it.

47:20.805 --> 47:22.842
I'm thinking. I'm thinking.

47:22.840 --> 47:24.842
Give me those.
I'll do it myself.

47:31.115 --> 47:33.721
[ Earth crumbling ]

47:34.118 --> 47:35.688
- [ Screams ]
- Hey, get back here!

47:37.955 --> 47:39.662
Come on!

47:39.657 --> 47:42.069
- [ Gunshots ]
- Get back here.

47:42.059 --> 47:43.197
Get, come on, come on.

47:43.194 --> 47:45.902
Anita:
Hurry! Come inside!

47:45.896 --> 47:47.466
- [ Gunshots continue ]
- Come on, come on.

47:47.698 --> 47:49.644
- [ Earth crumbling ]
- [ Screaming]

47:51.302 --> 47:53.304
[ Gunshots ]

47:53.637 --> 47:55.310
Anita:
What is he doing?

47:55.306 --> 47:57.343
Oh! what's going on?

47:57.341 --> 47:59.343
- [ Tire deflates ]
- What are the-- Oh!

47:59.343 --> 48:01.186
Just-- Just go.

48:01.178 --> 48:02.748
Oh, my God.

48:02.747 --> 48:04.249
This is crazed.

48:04.248 --> 48:07.229
Okay, does someone have
just a cell phone, a AAA card?

48:07.218 --> 48:09.061
So, what do we do now,
professor?

48:09.053 --> 48:11.033
Well, first,
stop waving those guns.

48:11.021 --> 48:13.023
I don't know.
I need to think for a minute.

48:13.023 --> 48:14.195
Oh, come on.

48:17.495 --> 48:18.906
Pretty hyped-up group.

48:18.896 --> 48:20.773
Yeah, they got good reason.

48:20.765 --> 48:22.767
I don't think we've been
properly introduced.

48:22.767 --> 48:24.212
I'm John.

48:24.201 --> 48:26.681
Shannon.
Pleased to meet you.

48:26.670 --> 48:28.377
50, what do you do

48:28.372 --> 48:30.943
when you're not fleeing
prehistoric monsters?

48:30.941 --> 48:32.420
Five to ten.

48:34.278 --> 48:36.224
♪♪

48:37.782 --> 48:39.784
[ Bell on door rings]

48:42.286 --> 48:43.890
I'll take this
when you guys are ready.

48:46.290 --> 48:47.769
[ Phone rings ]

48:47.925 --> 48:49.700
[ Phone beeps ]

48:50.861 --> 48:53.535
- Yours from Wilson, too?
- Yeah.

48:53.531 --> 48:55.204
Read it to me, will you?

48:55.199 --> 48:57.145
Left my glasses in the car.

48:59.203 --> 49:01.240
What?

49:01.238 --> 49:03.582
Nothing. I just thought
I saw something.

49:03.574 --> 49:05.076
Um...

49:05.075 --> 49:07.487
says the choppers
may have spotted a van

49:07.478 --> 49:09.082
parked nut
near Wrightson Swamp.

49:09.079 --> 49:11.286
So, did they land
and check it out?

49:11.282 --> 49:13.455
Negative. Wilson says the area
was too heavily wooded

49:13.451 --> 49:14.759
to put the choppers down.

49:15.986 --> 49:18.091
Pack up your chalupas.

49:18.088 --> 49:20.227
Let's blow this taco stand.

49:20.224 --> 49:21.567
Did you pay?

49:21.559 --> 49:22.560
It's your turn.

49:24.161 --> 49:25.299
It's always my turn.

49:32.670 --> 49:34.513
What's cooking?

49:34.505 --> 49:37.145
Just more peaches and beans.

49:37.141 --> 49:39.587
- Hold the beans, please.
- Yeah, me, too.

49:39.777 --> 49:41.916
[ Screen clangs ]

49:43.481 --> 49:45.154
My Lord.

49:45.149 --> 49:47.322
God bless Ronald Reagan.

49:47.318 --> 49:48.490
What is it?

49:48.486 --> 49:49.863
Two words...

49:52.456 --> 49:53.867
Merry Christmas.

49:57.328 --> 49:59.604
Well, this ought to even
the odds a little bit.

50:00.998 --> 50:02.636
And there's a lot more
in there.

50:03.834 --> 50:06.440
[ Birds chirping ]

50:13.177 --> 50:14.485
You okay?

50:16.180 --> 50:19.821
We're gonna get through this,
you and me.

50:19.817 --> 50:21.694
I'm tired.

50:21.685 --> 50:23.961
It wasn't supposed
to be this way.

50:23.954 --> 50:25.160
When you grow up
the prettiest girl

50:25.155 --> 50:26.828
in Martin Springs,

50:26.824 --> 50:29.532
you think everything's
gonna be a bed of roses.

50:29.527 --> 50:31.700
Marry the captain
of the football team

50:31.695 --> 50:33.971
and live happily ever after,

50:33.964 --> 50:36.137
but he turns out to be
a raging psychotic

50:36.133 --> 50:37.806
who gets
hooked on 0xyContin.

50:37.801 --> 50:39.041
Every night he heats you,

50:39.036 --> 50:41.676
and every morning,
he begs your forgiveness.

50:41.672 --> 50:42.878
You wake up wondering
if this is the day

50:42.873 --> 50:44.682
he finally kills you,

50:44.675 --> 50:47.588
and then you do
something about it.

50:47.578 --> 50:51.185
I'm tired of being so scared
all the damn time.

50:51.181 --> 50:53.684
I'm tired of just getting by
instead of living.

50:59.690 --> 51:03.001
[ Birds chirping ]

51:19.610 --> 51:22.591
Excuse me, if I could just
have a moment of your time.

51:28.586 --> 51:30.964
[ Gunshot ]

51:31.188 --> 51:32.531
What was that?

51:32.523 --> 51:33.934
I don't know.

51:36.727 --> 51:39.867
The man asked
for a moment of your time.

51:39.863 --> 51:42.366
Is that too much to ask?

51:42.366 --> 51:43.936
All right,
so if you don't mind

51:43.934 --> 51:45.538
giving my man Carl here

51:45.536 --> 51:48.779
your undivided attention,
that would be great.

51:48.772 --> 51:50.615
- Go ahead, sir.
- To begin with,

51:50.608 --> 51:52.747
the kidnapping
and prison escape

51:52.743 --> 51:54.745
is now officially over.

51:54.745 --> 51:56.418
Sorry, folks.
Better luck next time.

51:56.413 --> 51:58.086
The business
of getting out of here

51:58.082 --> 51:59.117
without getting eaten

51:59.116 --> 52:02.120
by whatever's outside
has begun.

52:02.119 --> 52:03.723
Where did you get those?

52:03.721 --> 52:05.064
Well, the owner
of this cabin

52:05.055 --> 52:07.262
is obviously
a crackerjack survivalist,

52:07.257 --> 52:09.430
and we found enough guns here
to start World War III.

52:09.426 --> 52:11.235
50, if you're good

52:11.228 --> 52:13.265
and promise not to shoot
each other in the head,

52:13.263 --> 52:16.301
my friend Carl will give you
the weapon of your choice.

52:16.300 --> 52:19.338
But should you choose to he
a fool or a hothead,

52:19.336 --> 52:21.907
<i>and I am talking
to you and you,</i>

52:21.905 --> 52:23.441
then my good friend Carl here

52:23.440 --> 52:25.283
will have to blow
your heads clean off.

52:25.275 --> 52:28.950
- And I will do that.
- So, that's that.

52:28.946 --> 52:31.517
Let's go into the kitchen
and load up.

52:36.253 --> 52:39.200
[ Door creaks open ]

52:43.127 --> 52:45.266
Well, it looks quiet enough.

52:45.262 --> 52:47.970
Maybe it went away,
just some dumb animal.

52:47.965 --> 52:49.205
Smart enough
to flatten our tires

52:49.199 --> 52:50.303
and maroon us here.

52:50.300 --> 52:52.644
Let's see if this
stirs the pot a little.

52:52.836 --> 52:54.782
[Wood clangs ]

53:04.815 --> 53:06.021
Must be gone.

53:06.183 --> 53:07.787
[ Explosion ]

53:07.985 --> 53:09.020
Wrung, buddy.

53:09.019 --> 53:11.158
Wrong in a big way, junior.

53:11.155 --> 53:13.829
I got a had feeling
about this.

53:13.824 --> 53:15.360
All right,
everyone hold your ears.

53:15.359 --> 53:17.202
Fire in the hole.

53:17.394 --> 53:19.203
[ Machine gun shots]

53:19.463 --> 53:21.204
[ Sharks growling ]

53:21.398 --> 53:23.878
It's just as I thought.
There's more than one.

53:23.867 --> 53:25.642
You gotta be kidding me.
How many?

53:25.636 --> 53:27.013
Six, seven,
maybe a whole mess of 'em

53:27.004 --> 53:28.210
by now, I don't know.

53:28.205 --> 53:29.741
All is I know is
when they smelled blood,

53:29.740 --> 53:31.651
this place became
tha hometown Buffet.

53:31.642 --> 53:33.178
We're never
getting out here now.

53:33.177 --> 53:35.054
- Damn.
- "Damn" is right, girl.

53:35.045 --> 53:36.388
You bitches hadn't done
what you done,

53:36.380 --> 53:38.326
I'd be sitting in a warm cell
right now

53:38.315 --> 53:39.851
waiting for my dinner
like these sharks.

53:39.850 --> 53:41.329
Carl: All right,
enough of the blame game.

53:41.318 --> 53:42.854
This is serious.

53:42.853 --> 53:45.060
We're almost out of food,

53:45.055 --> 53:46.932
and we're next on the menu.

53:46.924 --> 53:48.096
Hey, wait a minute.

53:48.092 --> 53:49.196
Anyone notice
if there's a well

53:49.193 --> 53:50.570
anywhere on this property?

53:50.561 --> 53:53.508
No well, but I think I saw
some sort of cave out back.

53:53.497 --> 53:56.376
- Cave, even better.
- Why's that?

53:56.366 --> 53:58.937
All right, everyone,
back porch right now.

53:58.936 --> 54:00.381
He's right.
Let's go. Hurry.

54:00.370 --> 54:01.542
- Come on.
- Come on. Hurry.

54:06.243 --> 54:08.189
[ Birds chirping ]

54:08.879 --> 54:11.052
What would you say, fellas?

54:11.048 --> 54:12.550
300 feet maybe.

54:12.549 --> 54:14.051
I'd say more like 400.

54:14.051 --> 54:16.258
- What do you think, professor?
- Well, I asked for a well

54:16.253 --> 54:17.891
'cause I was hoping
we could climb down

54:17.888 --> 54:19.595
and reach
the subterranean caverns

54:19.590 --> 54:21.069
that are known
to crisscross this area,

54:21.058 --> 54:22.560
but a cave's even better.

54:22.559 --> 54:24.095
It's sure
to lead us downward.

54:24.094 --> 54:25.732
But how do we all
get over there safely?

54:25.729 --> 54:26.764
And how do you know
that shark's

54:26.764 --> 54:28.243
not gonna follow us
into the cave?

54:28.232 --> 54:30.769
First question,
not exactly sure.

54:30.768 --> 54:32.247
Second question, cave floors

54:32.236 --> 54:33.874
usually consist
of solid stone,

54:33.871 --> 54:36.078
so sharks won't be able
to burrow through.

54:36.073 --> 54:38.053
Anita: Okay,
I've got a great idea.

54:38.041 --> 54:41.045
Why don't we just stay put
right here till help comes?

54:41.044 --> 54:43.650
Not a great idea, babe.

54:43.647 --> 54:45.285
We don't want
that kind of help.

54:45.282 --> 54:47.228
Oh, yeah, sorry.
I forgot.

54:47.217 --> 54:49.561
There's an even better reason
to leave soon.

54:49.553 --> 54:51.089
- Well, spit it out.
- Yeah, give, professor.

54:51.088 --> 54:52.567
What's got you so spooked?

54:52.556 --> 54:55.594
Well, every year,
sharks swarm,

54:55.592 --> 54:59.597
sometimes 15,000 in an area
less than two miles wide.

54:59.596 --> 55:02.577
They define
hunting territory, mate,

55:02.566 --> 55:04.512
devour everything in sight,
then move on.

55:04.501 --> 55:06.503
I'm concerned that what
we've got in the front yard

55:06.503 --> 55:07.914
is just a scouting party

55:07.905 --> 55:10.112
waiting on a thousand
of their dearest friends.

55:10.107 --> 55:11.313
No, this doesn't sound good
at all.

55:11.308 --> 55:13.151
- No, it doesn't.
- So, we gotta figure a way

55:13.143 --> 55:15.680
to get to that cave
without becoming fish food.

55:15.679 --> 55:16.623
Exactly.

55:16.613 --> 55:19.492
And how the hell
do we do that?

55:19.483 --> 55:21.156
Professor, you said sharks

55:21.151 --> 55:23.290
gravitate toward human blood,
right?

55:23.287 --> 55:24.857
Like ants to honey, Honey.

55:24.855 --> 55:27.301
So, let's just give 'em
what they want.

55:27.291 --> 55:28.770
What?

55:29.927 --> 55:31.838
Got 'em.

55:31.829 --> 55:33.001
I found this shirt.

55:35.666 --> 55:36.804
Pants.

55:38.101 --> 55:39.546
♪♪

55:39.770 --> 55:40.942
These might work.

55:43.440 --> 55:45.283
[ Metal tapping ]

55:45.475 --> 55:46.954
It's ready.

55:48.111 --> 55:49.647
[ Blood slurping ]

55:49.847 --> 55:51.326
Come and get it.

55:55.853 --> 55:57.355
Okay. Ready?

55:57.354 --> 55:58.458
Let's do it.

55:58.455 --> 55:59.957
Hey, guys, how's it
looking over there?

55:59.957 --> 56:01.129
Nothing in sight.

56:01.124 --> 56:03.126
Let's hope
it stays that way.

56:03.126 --> 56:04.469
Who's the best shot?

56:06.697 --> 56:09.473
- Just don't miss.
- I don't intend to.

56:09.466 --> 56:12.140
All right, everybody,
let's get ready to rumble.

56:12.135 --> 56:13.808
Okay, how do we know
exactly when?

56:13.804 --> 56:15.977
- Oh, you'll know.
- Don't worry.

56:15.973 --> 56:17.748
I'm not gonna let
anything happen to you.

56:21.578 --> 56:23.649
[ Blood squirting ]

56:32.723 --> 56:34.259
Stay frosty, everybody.

56:34.258 --> 56:35.862
Here goes nothing.

56:45.535 --> 56:47.515
[ Earth crumbles ]

56:48.772 --> 56:50.547
Oh, my God.
There are six of 'em.

56:52.609 --> 56:54.611
I sure hope Dirty Harriet
can shoot a gun

56:54.611 --> 56:56.056
as well as she
shoots her mouth off.

56:56.046 --> 56:57.047
Get ready.

56:57.047 --> 56:59.425
Don't sweat it.
I was born to do this.

56:59.416 --> 57:00.520
Better.

57:00.517 --> 57:02.588
Let's hope so
for everybody's sake.

57:04.521 --> 57:07.024
- [ Gunshot ]
- [ Explosion ]

57:07.224 --> 57:09.932
Right. Go, go, go.

57:10.127 --> 57:12.129
[ Door slams ]

57:12.362 --> 57:13.397
Nice work.

57:13.397 --> 57:14.774
Thank me later.

57:16.733 --> 57:17.973
Quick.

57:19.036 --> 57:20.413
- Quick.
- Go.

57:20.404 --> 57:21.883
Go, go.

57:23.540 --> 57:25.542
[ Earth crumbling ]

57:26.777 --> 57:28.779
[Girls screaming ]

57:30.147 --> 57:32.149
[ Shark growls ]

57:34.284 --> 57:36.264
[ Earth crumbling ]

57:37.054 --> 57:38.965
[ Man screams]

57:41.258 --> 57:43.238
[Groaning ]

57:44.728 --> 57:46.571
Oh, my God.
Come on, you guys.

57:46.563 --> 57:48.167
Here comes one now.
Hurry, hurry.

57:48.165 --> 57:49.735
Get up, get up.

57:49.733 --> 57:52.270
I think I sprained my ankle.

57:52.502 --> 57:54.311
[ Growling ]

57:54.504 --> 57:56.450
They're coming.

57:56.440 --> 57:57.680
Guys, one of 'em now.

57:57.674 --> 57:59.176
Hey, come on.
Come on, come on, come on.

57:59.176 --> 58:00.120
Sprain or no sprain,

58:00.110 --> 58:01.612
you gotta rise
to the occasion.

58:02.679 --> 58:03.783
- Come on.
- [ Gunshots ]

58:03.780 --> 58:04.952
- Let's go.
- Anita: Hurry.

58:05.115 --> 58:06.526
[ Growling ]

58:06.750 --> 58:09.253
- Honey, they're coming.
- [ Gunshots continue]

58:09.252 --> 58:11.323
- Hurry.
- Honey: But it won't stop.

58:11.321 --> 58:13.323
Won't stop.
Bullets aren't working.

58:13.323 --> 58:15.599
Just go.
Save yourself. Go.

58:15.592 --> 58:17.128
- I've gotta help him.
- No, stay here.

58:17.127 --> 58:18.504
- You'll get killed.
- I'm going.

58:18.495 --> 58:20.099
Michelle:
Bad idea.

58:20.931 --> 58:22.877
[ Gunshots ]

58:23.133 --> 58:24.373
Guys, get hack.

58:24.368 --> 58:26.348
Hey! Hey!

58:26.603 --> 58:28.139
[ Growling ]

58:28.338 --> 58:30.318
Look over here!

58:33.610 --> 58:36.181
John, no.
Get out of there.

58:36.380 --> 58:38.291
[ Growling ]

58:38.648 --> 58:40.286
[ Screams ]

58:40.517 --> 58:41.791
No.

58:42.786 --> 58:44.322
[ Wailing ]

58:44.521 --> 58:46.501
Come on, dollface,
help me get him up.

58:46.490 --> 58:47.798
What'd you call me?

58:51.828 --> 58:53.398
God help me.

58:53.397 --> 58:54.967
Come on, guys. Come on.

58:54.965 --> 58:57.138
Come on, come on,
come on, come on.

58:57.134 --> 58:58.909
- Wait. Wait.
- Come on, come on.

59:01.405 --> 59:03.351
[crying 1

59:07.177 --> 59:08.747
[ Earth crumbling ]

59:08.979 --> 59:11.425
He gave his life.

59:11.415 --> 59:13.554
I know.

59:13.550 --> 59:15.996
John was a fine young man.

59:15.986 --> 59:18.193
He left us much too soon.

59:18.188 --> 59:20.566
I'll mourn him
for the rest of my life,

59:20.557 --> 59:21.831
but I know
he'd want us to push on,

59:21.825 --> 59:23.031
so just follow me,

59:23.026 --> 59:24.835
and let's just get
tha hell out of here.

59:38.542 --> 59:39.782
You know,
if we go by the G.P.S.

59:39.776 --> 59:41.119
we got from Wilson,

59:41.111 --> 59:43.557
we're just about a mile away
from the coordinates.

59:43.547 --> 59:44.719
Is that so?

59:44.915 --> 59:46.360
Yeah, but don't you think
we should call him,

59:46.550 --> 59:48.587
let him know
we're going in without backup?

59:48.585 --> 59:49.859
- No.
- Why not?

59:49.853 --> 59:50.923
'Cause the minute
we call it in,

59:50.921 --> 59:52.025
every black-and-white
from here

59:52.022 --> 59:53.262
to Fort Smith
is gonna come blazing

59:53.256 --> 59:54.462
through these gullies

59:54.458 --> 59:56.199
like they're gunning
for Bonnie and Clyde.

59:56.193 --> 59:58.195
- Who?
- What?

59:58.195 --> 59:59.799
Who are Bonnie and Clyde?

59:59.796 --> 01:00:01.798
- How old are you?
- 29.

01:00:01.798 --> 01:00:03.573
And you've never heard
of Bonnie and Clyde?

01:00:03.567 --> 01:00:05.604
- No.
- How 'bout Ma Barker?

01:00:05.602 --> 01:00:08.048
- From "The Price is Right."
- Oh, for the love of--

01:00:10.307 --> 01:00:12.947
[ Bird crowing ]

01:00:13.143 --> 01:00:15.953
Hey, look.
White van, blue stripes.

01:00:15.946 --> 01:00:18.927
Oh, yeah. I see it.

01:00:23.887 --> 01:00:25.594
Where you going?

01:00:25.789 --> 01:00:26.563
[ Earth crumbling ]

01:00:26.756 --> 01:00:28.429
I don't know.
Just anxious, I guess.

01:00:28.425 --> 01:00:29.597
Well, relax.

01:00:29.593 --> 01:00:31.072
If they're in there,
we have to wait for them

01:00:31.061 --> 01:00:32.404
to make the first move.

01:00:33.797 --> 01:00:35.902
- If we wait for them--
- I said get your ass

01:00:35.899 --> 01:00:37.003
hack in here.

01:00:37.267 --> 01:00:37.904
[ Chomping ]

01:00:38.101 --> 01:00:39.136
Sorry.

01:00:39.136 --> 01:00:41.480
Give me the bi run-cs.

01:00:43.006 --> 01:00:44.110
Here.

01:00:46.643 --> 01:00:48.020
See anything?

01:00:48.011 --> 01:00:49.991
Well, we got a plate match.

01:00:49.980 --> 01:00:51.152
Then we got 'em.

01:00:51.148 --> 01:00:53.128
Not yet.

01:00:54.151 --> 01:00:56.028
- Huh.
- What?

01:00:56.019 --> 01:00:57.794
They got four flat tires,

01:00:57.787 --> 01:01:00.131
and there's something weird
laying in the front yard.

01:01:00.123 --> 01:01:03.104
Here. Take a look.
Tell me what you think it is.

01:01:05.328 --> 01:01:06.466
Adam:
That is strange.

01:01:06.463 --> 01:01:07.999
It looks like
a piece of a dummy

01:01:07.998 --> 01:01:09.306
all ripped up.

01:01:09.299 --> 01:01:11.210
That's exactly
what I thought.

01:01:11.434 --> 01:01:12.538
[ Earth crumbling ]

01:01:12.769 --> 01:01:14.180
So, how do you want
to play this?

01:01:14.171 --> 01:01:15.650
Like always.

01:01:15.839 --> 01:01:16.977
[ Crashes ]

01:01:17.174 --> 01:01:19.677
Did you see that?
What is that thing?

01:01:19.676 --> 01:01:20.677
Let's get out of here.

01:01:21.111 --> 01:01:23.057
[ Engine revs ]

01:01:35.192 --> 01:01:36.637
Wow.

01:01:36.626 --> 01:01:39.505
- This place is huge.
- Cavernous.

01:01:39.696 --> 01:01:41.539
♪♪

01:01:54.211 --> 01:01:56.157
You sure there's another way
out of here, Doc?

01:01:56.146 --> 01:01:58.217
It does, and I'd imagine
we just need to find one

01:01:58.215 --> 01:02:00.320
with easy access
to tha surface.

01:02:19.002 --> 01:02:21.505
So, once we're up top,
what next, girl?

01:02:21.504 --> 01:02:24.383
- Quiet.
- No.

01:02:24.374 --> 01:02:25.580
Quiet time's over.

01:02:25.575 --> 01:02:27.054
These people have worked
way too hard

01:02:27.043 --> 01:02:29.250
and lost too much
to have it end badly

01:02:29.246 --> 01:02:31.453
once you and Blondie here
take off to parts unknown.

01:02:31.448 --> 01:02:33.894
Listen, bitch,
I'm the one who came up

01:02:33.883 --> 01:02:35.089
with the escape plan.

01:02:35.085 --> 01:02:36.928
I'm the one who rescued us
from those sharks.

01:02:36.920 --> 01:02:39.958
Now, don't make me shoot you
out of lack of respect.

01:02:39.956 --> 01:02:42.596
Excuse me.

01:02:42.592 --> 01:02:44.401
The only one allowed
to shoot anybody

01:02:44.394 --> 01:02:46.635
anymore is me.

01:02:46.630 --> 01:02:48.371
And how do you figure that,
cop?

01:02:52.202 --> 01:02:53.738
Because you're out
of bullets.

01:02:53.737 --> 01:02:55.944
You blew your last round
shooting at the sharks.

01:02:55.939 --> 01:02:58.886
Okay, you need to give her
her weapon hack

01:02:58.875 --> 01:03:00.616
right now,

01:03:00.610 --> 01:03:03.648
along with whatever
leftover ammo you might have.

01:03:03.813 --> 01:03:05.121
[ Chuckling ]

01:03:05.315 --> 01:03:07.090
Do you really think
I'd give a psychotic like you

01:03:07.083 --> 01:03:08.460
live ammo?

01:03:08.451 --> 01:03:10.590
What? I was defenseless
hack there.

01:03:10.587 --> 01:03:11.759
No, you weren't.

01:03:11.755 --> 01:03:13.928
You had me, John,
Michelle, the professor.

01:03:13.923 --> 01:03:15.960
You don't have
any faith in me either?

01:03:15.959 --> 01:03:18.132
Sweetie,
I know your backstory.

01:03:18.128 --> 01:03:19.937
There's no way
you'd ever raise your gun

01:03:19.929 --> 01:03:21.499
to shoot at anything.

01:03:21.898 --> 01:03:23.809
[ Howling ]

01:03:24.100 --> 01:03:25.477
[ Low growl ]

01:03:25.735 --> 01:03:27.840
What the hell was that?

01:03:27.837 --> 01:03:29.942
It's those creatures.

01:03:29.939 --> 01:03:32.010
They're speaking
to each other like whales.

01:03:32.008 --> 01:03:34.648
- Crap on a cracker.
- For once, professor,

01:03:34.644 --> 01:03:35.987
I agree
with Honey's assessment.

01:03:35.979 --> 01:03:37.287
I say the sooner
we get out of here,

01:03:37.280 --> 01:03:39.658
- the better off we'll be.
- Speak for yourself.

01:03:39.649 --> 01:03:41.151
Yeah, Screw.

01:03:41.151 --> 01:03:42.994
There's a breeze
coming from this direction.

01:03:42.986 --> 01:03:44.090
Good possibility

01:03:44.087 --> 01:03:45.589
there's an opening
somewhere up ahead.

01:03:45.588 --> 01:03:47.329
All right.
You heard the man, ladies.

01:03:47.324 --> 01:03:48.325
Let's move.

01:03:53.096 --> 01:03:54.439
- You know what, boss?
- What?

01:03:54.431 --> 01:03:56.877
You're okay.
Thanks for the trust.

01:03:56.866 --> 01:03:58.812
You're welcome.

01:03:58.802 --> 01:04:00.509
Don't make me regret it.

01:04:00.503 --> 01:04:02.005
Thank you.

01:04:03.707 --> 01:04:05.653
♪♪

01:04:07.010 --> 01:04:08.512
[Water dripping ]

01:04:08.712 --> 01:04:10.453
[ Man groans]

01:04:42.245 --> 01:04:44.247
[ Water dripping louder ]

01:04:51.921 --> 01:04:53.867
[ Music fades]

01:04:56.993 --> 01:04:59.496
So, doc,
why so bright down here?

01:04:59.496 --> 01:05:01.339
Yeah, it looks like the walls
are lit from behind.

01:05:01.331 --> 01:05:02.537
Professor:
It's the phosphorous

01:05:02.532 --> 01:05:03.602
from the limestone.

01:05:03.600 --> 01:05:06.012
It creates its awn type
of cold light.

01:05:06.002 --> 01:05:08.004
Michelle: Learn something new
every day, huh?

01:05:13.209 --> 01:05:15.587
Sounds like water running.

01:05:15.578 --> 01:05:17.080
There's a good chance.

01:05:17.247 --> 01:05:19.227
[Water dripping ]

01:05:31.861 --> 01:05:34.535
Guess we're not
the first ones here, huh?

01:05:34.531 --> 01:05:36.033
Carl: No, I read they were
mining for minerals

01:05:36.032 --> 01:05:37.136
about a decade ago,

01:05:37.133 --> 01:05:38.942
but they didn't find anything
worthwhile.

01:05:38.935 --> 01:05:41.040
So, they just left their stuff
there and lit off?

01:05:41.037 --> 01:05:42.380
Guess so.

01:05:42.605 --> 01:05:44.414
[ Growling ]

01:05:47.444 --> 01:05:49.981
I don't blame 'em one bit.

01:05:49.979 --> 01:05:52.084
Is that water, professor?

01:05:52.081 --> 01:05:53.754
I think that's
an underground river.

01:05:53.750 --> 01:05:56.560
That could lead us
to the surface. Let's go.

01:06:07.931 --> 01:06:09.672
Hey, come here,
all of you.

01:06:09.666 --> 01:06:11.111
Is that daylight?

01:06:12.569 --> 01:06:15.277
- It sure is.
- Maybe we're saved.

01:06:15.271 --> 01:06:16.773
That's most definitely
a way out.

01:06:16.773 --> 01:06:18.116
- Only--
- Only what?

01:06:18.107 --> 01:06:19.586
Only to get to it,
we're all gonna have to wade

01:06:19.576 --> 01:06:21.283
through about 100 yards
of water waist-deep,

01:06:21.277 --> 01:06:22.278
maybe higher.

01:06:22.278 --> 01:06:23.518
You're thinking
some of our friends

01:06:23.513 --> 01:06:25.515
are just below the surface
lying in wait?

01:06:25.515 --> 01:06:26.755
It's a distinct possibility.

01:06:26.749 --> 01:06:28.990
Well, I don't see any fins.

01:06:28.985 --> 01:06:30.123
Oh, it doesn't matter.

01:06:30.119 --> 01:06:31.325
We could get ten feet out,

01:06:31.321 --> 01:06:32.800
and they'd be on us
before we knew what hit us.

01:06:32.789 --> 01:06:33.790
What can we do?

01:06:33.790 --> 01:06:35.770
Well,
we got a couple options.

01:06:35.758 --> 01:06:37.499
We can go back the way we came
and choose another path--

01:06:37.494 --> 01:06:39.337
No, no, no, no, no, no.
Miss me with that crap.

01:06:39.329 --> 01:06:40.672
That ain't happening.

01:06:40.663 --> 01:06:43.303
Oh, I actually agree
with you.

01:06:43.299 --> 01:06:45.336
Plus there's no guarantee
we'd find another exit.

01:06:45.335 --> 01:06:47.611
Or we may find more water
we can't get through.

01:06:47.604 --> 01:06:50.608
- Precisely.
- What's our other option?

01:06:50.607 --> 01:06:51.779
Send one of us through

01:06:51.774 --> 01:06:53.720
to test the waters,
if you get my drift.

01:06:53.710 --> 01:06:54.814
<i>Oh, I get it, all right.</i>

01:06:54.811 --> 01:06:55.983
One of us goes through,

01:06:55.979 --> 01:06:57.856
and if he or she
doesn't get eaten,

01:06:57.847 --> 01:06:59.520
we send the rest of 'em
through, right?

01:06:59.516 --> 01:07:01.189
I didn't say
it was a great option.

01:07:01.184 --> 01:07:03.391
Well, I, for one,
am not down

01:07:03.386 --> 01:07:05.388
for a fun game
of sharkasaurus roulette.

01:07:05.388 --> 01:07:07.459
Look, the water
may ultimately recede,

01:07:07.457 --> 01:07:08.959
but not necessarily
on our timeline.

01:07:08.958 --> 01:07:12.337
Okay, so what you're saying
is we'll run out of,

01:07:12.328 --> 01:07:14.740
like, food and air?

01:07:14.731 --> 01:07:16.711
Air, we got.
We got plenty of water.

01:07:16.699 --> 01:07:20.010
Food, I got a protein bar
and a pack of Twinkies.

01:07:20.003 --> 01:07:21.641
Yeah, I'm in the same boat.

01:07:21.638 --> 01:07:23.515
All I've got left
is half a pack of Tic Tacs.

01:07:23.506 --> 01:07:24.746
Wait a minute.

01:07:24.741 --> 01:07:26.186
Michelle, you may be
on to something.

01:07:26.175 --> 01:07:27.882
What? Tic Tacs?

01:07:27.877 --> 01:07:29.322
Yeah, I don't think sharks
eat Tic Tacs.

01:07:29.312 --> 01:07:31.656
No, you said, "Boat."

01:07:31.848 --> 01:07:35.057
- We got a raft.
- Oh, shoot. That's right.

01:07:35.251 --> 01:07:36.696
Well, let's go get it.

01:07:36.686 --> 01:07:39.166
Easy now.
You two stay here.

01:07:39.155 --> 01:07:40.600
You monitor the water.

01:07:40.590 --> 01:07:43.696
You see a ripple, vibration,
anything, you take note.

01:07:43.693 --> 01:07:45.195
Aren't you afraid
we'll try to escape?

01:07:45.194 --> 01:07:47.333
Nope, not at all.

01:08:06.449 --> 01:08:09.794
- You still see it?
- No, I think it's gone.

01:08:09.786 --> 01:08:11.094
Jeez, what was that thing?

01:08:11.087 --> 01:08:12.794
I don't know,
but if I didn't know better,

01:08:12.789 --> 01:08:13.927
I'd think we just had
an encounter

01:08:13.923 --> 01:08:15.903
with a land shark.

01:08:15.892 --> 01:08:17.303
A land shark?

01:08:17.292 --> 01:08:19.398
I mean, what, you mean like
from "Saturday Night Live"?

01:08:19.395 --> 01:08:21.705
Oh, that, you remember?

01:08:21.698 --> 01:08:24.542
So, that guy was right.
It is a shark.

01:08:24.533 --> 01:08:25.638
Oh, we gotta warn somebody.

01:08:25.635 --> 01:08:27.238
What are we gonna say?
Who's gonna believe us?

01:08:27.236 --> 01:08:28.874
I mean, they're gonna think
we skipped the donuts

01:08:28.871 --> 01:08:30.747
and went right
for the hard stuff.

01:08:30.740 --> 01:08:33.448
Yeah, but I mean, it was real.
We saw it. We felt it.

01:08:33.443 --> 01:08:34.615
Yeah, and if we did,

01:08:34.611 --> 01:08:36.818
I'm sure the escaped convicts
did as well.

01:08:36.813 --> 01:08:38.292
Wait. You mean...

01:08:38.281 --> 01:08:39.783
I think that that thing,
it took away

01:08:39.782 --> 01:08:40.760
their only means of escape,

01:08:40.750 --> 01:08:43.822
and it trapped them
in the hideout.

01:08:43.819 --> 01:08:45.890
50, that ripped-up dummy
that we saw,

01:08:45.888 --> 01:08:48.163
what was that,
some sort of a decoy?

01:08:48.157 --> 01:08:49.830
I'd stake my pension on it.

01:08:49.826 --> 01:08:51.567
What do you think?
Are they still trapped inside?

01:08:51.560 --> 01:08:52.767
Hard to tell.

01:08:52.761 --> 01:08:54.069
Pull up
the geological schematics

01:08:54.063 --> 01:08:55.804
on that fancy gadget
of yours.

01:08:55.798 --> 01:08:57.970
- You mean the iPad?
- Whatever.

01:08:57.966 --> 01:08:59.310
See if there's anyplace

01:08:59.301 --> 01:09:01.975
they could have escaped to
given the chance.

01:09:01.970 --> 01:09:03.951
- Come on.
- All right, all right.

01:09:03.939 --> 01:09:05.010
According to this,

01:09:05.008 --> 01:09:06.988
there is a cave entrance

01:09:06.975 --> 01:09:08.819
about 200 yards
from the back of the cabin.

01:09:08.810 --> 01:09:10.346
That's it, then.

01:09:10.345 --> 01:09:11.416
What's it?

01:09:11.413 --> 01:09:12.825
They threw the dummy
to the wolf,

01:09:12.814 --> 01:09:14.260
and they made a run for it.

01:09:14.250 --> 01:09:16.491
Well, assuming they made it,
where do you think they went?

01:09:16.486 --> 01:09:18.158
If it were me,
I'd use that cave

01:09:18.154 --> 01:09:19.827
to get the heck out of there
as quick as I could.

01:09:19.822 --> 01:09:21.801
I mean, not only
do they have us hunting them,

01:09:21.791 --> 01:09:24.828
they've got that creature
hunting them, too.

01:09:24.827 --> 01:09:26.636
Where did they come from?

01:09:26.629 --> 01:09:29.303
I think Hell'd
be a good place to start.

01:09:32.035 --> 01:09:34.015
[ Birds chirping ]

01:09:36.639 --> 01:09:38.618
[ Water rippling ]

01:09:39.142 --> 01:09:40.450
Se?

01:09:40.443 --> 01:09:42.046
Well, it looks sound enough,

01:09:42.045 --> 01:09:44.149
provided those things
don't slice it in half.

01:09:44.147 --> 01:09:45.819
Distinct possibility,
my friend.

01:09:45.814 --> 01:09:47.453
Distinct possibility.

01:09:47.450 --> 01:09:49.157
Yeah, and we have oars,

01:09:49.152 --> 01:09:50.221
so I don't have
to stick my hands

01:09:50.219 --> 01:09:51.288
in the water.

01:09:51.287 --> 01:09:53.198
Yeah, I wouldn't suggest
doing that.

01:09:53.189 --> 01:09:55.226
Yeah, why make yourself
an appetizer?

01:09:55.224 --> 01:09:57.033
Look, I found some rope,
lots of it.

01:09:57.026 --> 01:09:59.529
Good girl, Michelle.
Bring it all.

01:09:59.529 --> 01:10:00.837
It'll make things
a hell of a lot easier.

01:10:00.830 --> 01:10:02.173
Sounds good to me.

01:10:02.165 --> 01:10:04.202
You ready to see
daylight again, professor?

01:10:04.200 --> 01:10:06.510
Oh, I'm looking forward
to it.

01:10:06.703 --> 01:10:08.182
- [ Water splashes ]
- [Shark growls]

01:10:08.371 --> 01:10:09.748
[Girls scream ]

01:10:10.173 --> 01:10:12.175
[ Machine gunshots ]

01:10:13.576 --> 01:10:15.886
Oh, my God.
Did you just hear that?

01:10:15.878 --> 01:10:18.825
- Yeah.
- Do you think that maybe--

01:10:18.815 --> 01:10:20.692
I don't know. I don't know.

01:10:20.683 --> 01:10:22.526
I don't know.

01:10:22.518 --> 01:10:27.263
Honey, we are officially
in the sauce.

01:10:27.256 --> 01:10:29.497
Take it easy, baby.

01:10:29.492 --> 01:10:31.699
If we have to go this alone,
we will.

01:10:31.694 --> 01:10:34.197
- Yeah, but how are we gonna--
- Put a hold on the play.

01:10:34.197 --> 01:10:36.677
I still got a good feeling
about this.

01:10:36.666 --> 01:10:38.373
He may be a relic,

01:10:38.367 --> 01:10:40.870
but that old guard
has what it takes.

01:10:40.870 --> 01:10:42.907
I hope you're right.

01:10:46.242 --> 01:10:48.222
[crying ]

01:10:50.580 --> 01:10:51.718
Come on, Sham.

01:10:51.714 --> 01:10:53.421
You can't afford
to go to pieces right now.

01:10:53.416 --> 01:10:54.918
We've come too far.

01:10:54.917 --> 01:10:58.455
Just leave me. I don't care.
I don't care.

01:10:58.454 --> 01:10:59.524
Look at me, little girl.

01:10:59.522 --> 01:11:00.899
I know
you didn't ask for this,

01:11:00.890 --> 01:11:02.062
but we're here.

01:11:02.058 --> 01:11:03.366
Now, we gotta make
the best of it.

01:11:03.359 --> 01:11:04.565
And that young man
who put his life

01:11:04.560 --> 01:11:05.903
on the line for you,

01:11:05.895 --> 01:11:08.205
he wouldn't want you
to give up,

01:11:08.197 --> 01:11:09.699
and neither do I.

01:11:09.699 --> 01:11:11.406
That goes ditto for me,
girl.

01:11:11.400 --> 01:11:14.609
50, dry those eyes,
and let's get topside, okay?

01:11:14.604 --> 01:11:16.982
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

01:11:16.973 --> 01:11:18.714
It's okay. It's okay.
Don't worry.

01:11:18.708 --> 01:11:19.743
Now, listen,
we get out of here

01:11:19.742 --> 01:11:20.777
in one piece,

01:11:20.777 --> 01:11:22.256
I'll have a nice, long talk
with the warden

01:11:22.245 --> 01:11:23.952
about your case, okay?

01:11:23.946 --> 01:11:25.550
Michelle:
Hey, what about me?

01:11:25.548 --> 01:11:27.459
No love
for your lotus blossom?

01:11:27.450 --> 01:11:28.929
You, too, Michelle.

01:11:28.918 --> 01:11:30.124
You, too.

01:11:37.560 --> 01:11:39.665
Anita:
There hasn't been a ripple.

01:11:39.662 --> 01:11:41.107
Maybe we should
just risk it.

01:11:43.132 --> 01:11:44.805
Personally, I'd rather wait
for the raft.

01:11:44.801 --> 01:11:48.339
Yeah, the raft
that may or may not be coming.

01:11:49.472 --> 01:11:51.679
Hey, you two.

01:11:53.810 --> 01:11:54.811
Honey:
Praise the Lord.

01:11:54.811 --> 01:11:56.688
I thought you were
never coming back.

01:11:58.114 --> 01:11:58.990
[Sighs]

01:12:02.151 --> 01:12:03.687
Where's the professor?

01:12:03.686 --> 01:12:06.132
He didn't make it.

01:12:06.122 --> 01:12:09.103
We heard gunshots.
What happened?

01:12:09.091 --> 01:12:10.968
Let's just leave it at,
"He didn't make it."

01:12:10.960 --> 01:12:12.166
Okay, well,

01:12:12.161 --> 01:12:13.697
how are we gonna get
this party started?

01:12:13.696 --> 01:12:15.869
Okay, listen,
I'll go first, all right?

01:12:15.865 --> 01:12:17.435
If I get across safely,

01:12:17.433 --> 01:12:19.276
tie a rape
to both ends of the boat,

01:12:19.268 --> 01:12:20.713
pull you all across.

01:12:20.703 --> 01:12:22.273
- In this thing?
- [ Sighs ]

01:12:22.271 --> 01:12:23.978
Good idea.

01:12:23.973 --> 01:12:25.714
Michelle,
help me with the ropes.

01:12:25.708 --> 01:12:27.016
Done.

01:12:30.980 --> 01:12:33.119
All right, make a left
at the mile marker.

01:12:33.115 --> 01:12:34.822
- You sure?
- Yeah, I'm sure.

01:12:34.817 --> 01:12:36.353
According to the geological
survey map,

01:12:36.352 --> 01:12:37.490
there's an entrance
to the cave

01:12:37.486 --> 01:12:39.159
about a half a mile
west of here.

01:12:39.155 --> 01:12:41.157
Okeydokey.

01:12:41.157 --> 01:12:44.536
Just watch out for any more
of those land sharks.

01:12:44.527 --> 01:12:46.837
- You had to remind me.
- How could you forget?

01:12:59.742 --> 01:13:00.880
Now,
if something goes wrong,

01:13:00.877 --> 01:13:02.015
I'm counting on you.

01:13:02.011 --> 01:13:03.581
Pull me back
with all you got.

01:13:03.579 --> 01:13:04.819
We've got your back, sir.

01:13:04.814 --> 01:13:05.986
Good luck.

01:13:11.654 --> 01:13:13.600
[ Water splashes ]

01:14:04.106 --> 01:14:06.108
- He made it.
- That, he did.

01:14:06.108 --> 01:14:08.645
See, I told you
he had the guts.

01:14:08.644 --> 01:14:11.716
Okay, pull the boat back.

01:14:11.714 --> 01:14:13.091
Come across two by two.

01:14:13.082 --> 01:14:14.083
Will do.

01:14:21.490 --> 01:14:22.901
Honey:
Come on, pull.

01:14:29.465 --> 01:14:32.571
All right, ladies.
See you on the other side.

01:14:43.479 --> 01:14:44.583
Gut it?

01:14:49.452 --> 01:14:51.432
[Groans]

01:14:57.526 --> 01:14:58.937
[ Sharks howl ]

01:14:59.128 --> 01:15:01.267
Oh, what is that?

01:15:01.263 --> 01:15:04.369
I don't know.
Let's just keep on rowing.

01:15:04.367 --> 01:15:06.438
- Oh, my God.
- No, no, no. Don't worry.

01:15:06.435 --> 01:15:08.005
- Oh, my God.
- Don't get scared.

01:15:08.004 --> 01:15:10.177
No, let's go.
We can do this.

01:15:20.883 --> 01:15:23.523
[Groaning ]

01:15:38.501 --> 01:15:40.481
[Groans]

01:15:44.173 --> 01:15:45.709
Okay, I got it.

01:15:47.143 --> 01:15:48.178
I see him.

01:15:48.177 --> 01:15:49.178
There he is.
Go, go, go.

01:15:49.178 --> 01:15:50.555
I'm going.

01:15:55.651 --> 01:15:57.392
Oh, my God.

01:15:59.021 --> 01:16:00.398
Come on, come on,
come on, come on, come on.

01:16:00.389 --> 01:16:01.891
We're almost there.
We made it. We made it.

01:16:01.891 --> 01:16:03.734
- We got it.
- Give me your hand.

01:16:03.726 --> 01:16:05.501
Here we go.

01:16:08.664 --> 01:16:09.938
All right, pull it back.

01:16:11.834 --> 01:16:13.780
[ Panting out of breath ]

01:16:22.445 --> 01:16:24.948
All right, baby,
time to get the hell out.

01:16:24.947 --> 01:16:26.517
I'm right behind you.

01:16:38.727 --> 01:16:40.206
Come on. come on.

01:16:40.196 --> 01:16:42.472
Come on. We gut this.

01:16:50.806 --> 01:16:52.786
[ Low growl ]

01:17:08.958 --> 01:17:10.938
[Sighs]

01:17:15.598 --> 01:17:16.906
Whoa.

01:17:21.570 --> 01:17:23.811
- Whoa.
- Watch out.

01:17:25.808 --> 01:17:27.788
[ Machine gunshots ]

01:17:27.943 --> 01:17:29.684
[ Screaming ]

01:17:30.613 --> 01:17:32.183
Shannon.

01:17:32.414 --> 01:17:34.189
[ Screaming ]

01:17:34.583 --> 01:17:37.029
Anita.

01:17:41.490 --> 01:17:43.470
- [Woman screams]
- [ Splash ]

01:17:51.367 --> 01:17:53.369
[ Sniffling ]

01:17:55.871 --> 01:17:57.475
[ Cries ]

01:17:57.673 --> 01:17:59.346
Let's get the hell
out of here.

01:18:08.450 --> 01:18:10.157
Give me your hand.

01:18:10.386 --> 01:18:12.229
[Woman grunts]

01:18:18.394 --> 01:18:20.374
[ Bird crows ]

01:18:24.066 --> 01:18:26.046
[ Man grunts]

01:18:27.203 --> 01:18:29.149
[Sighs]

01:18:29.538 --> 01:18:31.518
[Sighs]

01:18:34.543 --> 01:18:36.716
Suppose you'll be wanting this
back now.

01:18:38.147 --> 01:18:40.559
You know, I been thinking...

01:18:40.549 --> 01:18:44.497
it's too bad everyone but me
had to die down there.

01:18:45.721 --> 01:18:48.668
Only Shannon's body
to recover,

01:18:48.657 --> 01:18:52.662
the rest devoured
by those creatures.

01:18:52.661 --> 01:18:56.370
It's gonna make recovery
and identification

01:18:56.365 --> 01:18:57.867
damn near impossible.

01:18:59.702 --> 01:19:02.546
The girl I feel
most sorry for

01:19:02.538 --> 01:19:04.347
is the one with a kid
waiting for her.

01:19:05.107 --> 01:19:07.417
Child needs a mom
to grow up well.

01:19:09.912 --> 01:19:14.361
So, I'm gonna turn around now

01:19:14.350 --> 01:19:16.523
and start looking for help.

01:19:16.518 --> 01:19:20.022
If I see one
of those damn land sharks,

01:19:20.022 --> 01:19:21.092
I'm gonna look
that son of a bitch

01:19:21.090 --> 01:19:24.230
right in the eye
and tell him to bugger off.

01:19:24.226 --> 01:19:25.569
Hell.

01:19:26.595 --> 01:19:28.871
I fought
with Michelle Alika.

01:19:29.064 --> 01:19:30.873
[ Chuckles ]

01:19:35.738 --> 01:19:37.115
Thank you.

01:20:14.143 --> 01:20:15.952
You all right, buddy?

01:20:15.944 --> 01:20:17.514
The prisoners?

01:20:17.513 --> 01:20:19.288
I'm the only one.

01:20:20.749 --> 01:20:22.922
Do you know what
we're up against?

01:20:24.119 --> 01:20:25.598
Yep.

01:20:31.126 --> 01:20:33.106
[ Earth crumbling ]

01:20:34.096 --> 01:20:36.042
[ Growl ]

01:20:37.266 --> 01:20:39.212
[ Gasping ]

01:20:45.207 --> 01:20:46.811
Crap on a cracker.

01:20:48.043 --> 01:20:49.989
♪♪
